title: apricot sticks
directions: Through food chopper, using medium blade, force dried apricots and seeded, medium, whole orange.
Put through chopper a second time.
Put in top of double boiler and stir in sugar.
Put over boiling water and cook, covered, 30 minutes or until quite stiff. Cool and stir in chopped nuts.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in layers for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bagels
directions: Bring honey and water to a boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Drop in bagels 4 at a time for 7 minutes, turning once.
Drain.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clams casino
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add crackers.
Drain clams, reserving 4 tablespoons juice.
Add clams, clam juice, wine and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir to blend ingredients well.
Stuff clam shells; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole #1
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except broccoli.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Put broccoli in casserole dish and pour ingredients over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: party quiche
directions: In a medium skillet, saute bacon and onion until most of the fat is cooked out of bacon, 7 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat; drain. Stir flour into drained bacon mixture.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; stir in milk, salt, pepper, Swiss cheese and bacon mixture. Preheat oven to 350°.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out pastry to 17 x 12-inch rectangle. Fit onto an ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking sheet with raised sides. Turn under and crimp edge of pastry.

Brush with unbeaten egg white. Spoon cheese filling evenly over coated pastry. Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in preheated oven until filling is partially set and surface is golden brown. Filling will continue to bake when removed from oven.

title: marylou's gooey butter cake
directions: Melt butter and beat in cake mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cream cheese with eggs and pour over cake.
Top with powdered sugar and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add sauce and water together and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine other ingredients.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spray pan with nonstick spray.
Spread evenly 1 cup sauce on bottom of pan.
Layer noodles, sauce, cheese filling, noodles, etc.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve in 2 cups hot water the Jell-O and add can of cranberries.
When firm, but not set, whip in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl or mold to set.

title: german icebox slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onions in salad bowl. Sprinkle with 7/8 cup sugar.
Combine vinegar, salad oil, dry mustard, celery seed, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling point.
Pour over slaw.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Keeps 1 week.

title: salmon shepherd's pie
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Prepare frozen peas as directed on package.
Combine celery, salmon, mushrooms, salt and pepper with cooked peas.
Stir onions into prepared potatoes; mix well.
Spoon salmon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Spoon potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned and casserole contents bubble.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Drain green beans. Melt oleo and add flour, salt, pepper, sour cream, sugar and grated onion. Fold beans into the mixture. Spread in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with Swiss cheese. Combine melted butter and cornflakes and top with bean mixture. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Chop all corned beef in food processor until fine.
Set aside.
Chop up green onions in food processor.
Stir 3/4 of the chopped corned beef and all the onion into the softened cream cheese and blend well.
Form into a ball. Chill 20 minutes, then roll it into the remaining corned beef. Better if made the day or night before.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Bake crust about 3 minutes.
Cut zucchini into slices.
Saute in margarine with chives, salt, pepper and oregano.
Combine sour cream, eggs and baking powder; mix well.
Combine zucchini mixture and cheese.
Place in partially cooked pie shell.
Top with Parmesan cheese and sprinkle generously with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sue's green beans
directions: Drain beans and place in 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar.
Pour mixture over beans. Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Bake covered at 350 for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes at 375.

title: magic cookie bars or hello dollys
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly with graham cracker crumbs, then sprinkle nuts over crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over nuts, then sprinkle coconut over the chips. Last, pour Eagle Brand evaporated milk over it and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 15 minutes and cut into squares.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients (except brown sugar and nuts) for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: party wienies
directions: Wrap hot dog in half slice of bacon.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Place in oven baking dish.
Sprinkle good amount of brown sugar over top with dash of dry mustard.
Let sit in fridge for 1/2 hour.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix cheese, 1 egg and sugar.
Add other 2 eggs and vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Put cupcake papers in a muffin tin.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake paper.
Pour batter in each about 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown. Allow to cool, then add topping and chill.
Makes 18.

title: easy refrigerator cinnamon rolls(a no-knead yeast product)
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and oleo or butter.
Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add cooled milk mixture to yeast along with egg and 2 cups unsifted flour.
Mix well and add 2 additional cups flour or enough to make a stiff batter.
Cover tightly with waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Refrigerate dough at least 2 hours. (I usually let it in refrigerator overnight.)
Take from refrigerator and roll half of mixture on floured board.
Melt oleo or butter and spread over all.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar and roll up.
Cut off in slices and put in greased pan to rise.
Bake until done and frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix all together and cool for at least 2 hours.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
In shallow baking or roasting pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Garnish, if desired, with fresh parsley.

title: mexican wedding cake cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and all other ingredients together with a large spoon.
If lumpy, you can continue with an electric mixer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding as box instructs except use 1/2 the amount of milk called for and use whipped cream to make a soft blend (about 1/2 cup whip cream). Put into pie crust and chill. Pudding will set up. Makes a great chocolate pie in half the time.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir into first mixture.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown, but still soft at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together alternately with milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring. Bake, in a tube pan that has been greased and floured, for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix remainder of ingredients with the hamburger.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: apple spice rice
directions: Melt butter. Stir in rice, onion, garlic and apples. Saute for 4 mins. Stir in chicken broth. Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer. 20 mins. until juice is absorbed.

title: jello salad - 3 layers
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour into pan and let set until firm.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket.
Drain off water.
Peel and chunk while still hot.
In large bowl, layer potatoes, celery and onion. Sprinkle salt, pepper and vinegar over this until all is used. Let stand in refrigerator overnight or until thoroughly cooled. Add sweet pickles.
Mix mustard and Miracle Whip to potato mixture.
Mix well and serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In saucepan bring to a boil milk and margarine.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast in warm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt together in a large bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Add yeast, mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time, and mix well.
Put on well floured board and knead for 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth.
Put into a slightly greased bowl and grease with margarine.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knock down, roll out, and shape as desired.
Dip in melted margarine.
Put into greased pan.
Cover and let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cupcakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Spoon into cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water; set aside.
Heat soup to boiling.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add gelatine, shrimp, celery and onion, then salad dressing.
Chill 5 hours or overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: smoked pork chops
directions: Put chops in rectangular pan and cover liberally with Worcestershire sauce.
(Cover all of the chops.)
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, oil and water.
Pour over and mix into sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add buttermilk, salt, soda and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan, 13 x 15-inch at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: curried macaroni bean salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Immediately toss with cheese and salt.
Drain kidney beans, reserving juice.
Combine beans, onion and celery to elbow macaroni in medium bowl.
Pour juice from beans into measuring cup and add water to equal 1 cup.
Heat juice to boiling in small saucepan.
Stir in curry powder, honey and vinegar; return to boiling.
Add raisins; simmer over low heat 5 to 7 minutes or until raisins are plump.
Pour dressing over macaroni mixture in bowl; toss well.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, stir together the cereal, milk and honey.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Portion batter evenly in 12 greased muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: shake 'em bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease a 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: turkey sausage, vegetable, pasta ragout casserole
directions: Preheat broiler.
Score the sausages 1/4-inch deep 3 times on each side.
Broil sausages about 4 inches from heat source until golden brown, 4 to 5 minutes per side.
Remove from broiler and cut into 1 inch lengths.
Reserve.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Dice potatoes, carrots, squash and onions; cook until tender.
Mix with chicken broth, chicken, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to make right consistency.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in a pizza pan to make a crust.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch mix.
Spread over dough.
Add various vegetables; sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer except chips and nuts.
Then stir in chips.
Sprinkle nuts on the bottom of a greased Bundt pan.
Pour in cake mix and bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: seafoam cole slaw
directions: Stir gelatin, salt and water together until dissolved.
Add ice water.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, onion and celery seed, beating slightly to blend well.
Chill until just beginning to congeal.
Fold in cabbage.
Pour into 3-cup mold and chill until firm.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in nuts and orange peel.
Combine egg, juice and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: quick cinnamon pecan rolls
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with some pudding.
Melt butter; dissolve sugar and cinnamon in butter. Drizzle over pudding.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover pan loosely with tinfoil.
Leave sitting out overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jambalaya new orleans style
directions: Cook rice in stock or bouillon cubes; set aside.
Saute ingredients down to shrimp in oleo or butter.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly 10 to 15 minutes, then add cooked rice and 1/4 stick butter.
Mix very well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together dressing, oil, garlic and dill.
Pour over crackers.
Stir until crackers soak up all liquid.

title: bourbon-marinated steak
directions: Place steak in glass or ceramic bowl or Ziploc plastic bag. Mix marinade ingredients and pour over steak.
Marinate, covered and refrigerated, 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove from refrigerator 20 to 30 minutes before cooking.
Grill steak over a hot fire until desired doneness, turning and brushing with remaining marinade.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to mug of hot water.
Makes a nice gift.

title: date-filled oatmeal bars
directions: Combine
flour,
oats, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Press half of mixture into an ungreased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine
dates, 1 cup sugar and water in a medium saucepan; cook
over	low heat until sugar dissolves and dates are soft. Mixture
should be thick and mushy.
Spread mixture evenly over dough in pan;
cover with remaining oats mixture. Bake at
325° for
minutes or until lightly browned.	Cut into 2
x
1-inch bars
while
warm.	Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: grapes 'n' spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Toss with grapes, apple, peanuts, green onion and sesame seed.
Toss with dressing to coat well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mince garlic and onion; add to cheese.
Add Ro-Tel.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: delicious dip
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients; set aside to drain in a colander. Cook the eggs, sugar and vinegar on medium to low heat until thick.
Take from heat; add cream cheese, then the pepper-onion mixture and butter.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg, salt, vanilla, anise oil and baking powder, mixing well with an electric mixer or by hand. Alternately add milk and flour until all are used.
Turn out on a floured board and use approximately 2 more cups flour to make dough soft and pliable.
If you want to make the dough variegated, add red coloring and work through to a variegated stage.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Fry down and crumble pork sausage.
Add smoked sausage which has been sliced or diced thinly.
Fry awhile with pork sausage. Add chopped seasonings to this and fry until wilted.
Add raw rice and fry with the rest until rice starts to get white (about 5 minutes).
Add 1 cup diced Ro-Tel tomatoes and 3 cups of water. Bring to a boil; add 2 beef bouillon cubes.
Cover and simmer until rice is completely cooked, 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes so that rice will cook evenly.
Do not add salt or pepper until you have tasted the finished product.

title: penna dutch casserole
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a small amount of salted water in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet; saute green pepper, onion and celery.
Brown sausage, drain off excess grease.
Put alternate layers of cabbage and vegetables and sausage mixture in a greased baking dish or Dutch oven, on top of the already cooked egg noodles.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over vegetable, sausage and cabbage mixture.
After all have been placed in pan, pour tomato juice on top, to cover everything.
Cook for one hour at 350°.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumber slices with sugar and salt. Add vinegar. Press slices with back of spoon to release juices. Cover tightly and chill about 4 hours. Yields about 4 servings.

title: summer mexican salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain on paper towels.
Cool and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with salsa, Ranch or French dressing and Doritos.

title: baked hash
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in casserole.
Put Worcestershire sauce in, if desired.
Bake until vegetables are tender and brown on top about 1 hour.

title: cheese log
directions: Divide Velveeta into three parts.
Roll between waxed paper (pie crust thickness).
Spread cream cheese to desired thickness over Velveeta.
Roll up each into a log.
Cut off ends (for appearance).
Serve with crackers.

title: mrs. skidmore's cucumber cinnamon ring pickles
directions: Peel large cucumbers. Cut in half crosswise. Scrape insides out.
Cut into slices (rings) approximately 1/3-inch thick to make 2 gallons.
Soak in 8 1/2 quarts of water for 24 hours. Drain and wash. Soak in tap water 3 hours and drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, food coloring, alum and enough water to cover. Simmer for 2 hours. (May need to divide into 2 pots.)
Drain and discard water.
Mix cinnamon sticks, 3 cups vinegar, sugar, candies and 3 cups water. Add to rings and boil until rings turn clear (takes 15 to 20 minutes). Fill jars and add 4 whole cloves to each pint. Seal jars.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk with chocolate and beat until smooth.
Add other ingredients and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Makes 1 pie.

title: saffron bread or buns
directions: Add saffron to boiling water.
Allow to steep for 8 to 12 hours.
Scald milk; add margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and salt.
Stir to melt margarine.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large bowl; add yeast to 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let set for 5 minutes or until foamy.
Add cooled milk mixture, steeped saffron and eggs to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups flour; mix well. Add raisins and/or candied fruit that have been dredged with flour.
(Raisins will be soft if allowed to set in hot water for a few minutes.
Drain and dredge with flour.) Add remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour. Punch down.
Form into loaves or buns; put into greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
The time will vary depending on size of loaf pan and whether loaves or buns.

title: spanish sangria
directions: Put
fruit slices in 1/2 gallon pitcher.
Add sugar and vermouth, then stir with wooden spoon, mashing fruit slightly. Add wine
and	marinate
up to 1 hour.
Fill pitcher with ice cubes; stir.
When
well	chilled,
serve.
Leave
spoon	in pitcher to catch fruit slices.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk together.
Boil for 1 minute. Take off heat.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and nuts.
Beat until stiff. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
This also may be used as candy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well. Gradually add granulated sugar and brown sugar. Cream thoroughly after each addition. Add eggs and milk, mixing well. Sift together the flour and soda. Blend with first mixture. Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets or roll the dough into balls 3/4 to 1 inch in size.
Press lightly with a fork to flatten. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, sugar, vanilla and meringue, adding the nuts last.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: garden special
directions: Dice peppers, onions and celery (coarse stalks and leaves may be used).
Add water and cook together for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, which have been peeled and cut up (not too small), and seasonings.
After it all comes to a boil, put in hot jars and process (30 minutes for quart jars and 25 minutes for pints).

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and put in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle almonds over onions. Spread soup on top. Add margarine.
Sprinkle with corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt; fold in whipped cream.
Then fold into apple mixture and chill.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Roll out in 2 long rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
The next day, wrap the rolls in aluminum foil, poking holes here and there.
Place in a shallow pan with a little water in the bottom and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a casserole.
Put melted butter or margarine over mixture with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: About 50 minutes before serving:
In large skillet over medium heat, brown sausage balls, one half at a time, until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Pour fat from skillet.
Return all balls to skillet.
Add catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple chunks.
Simmer covered until heated through.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan. Cut bread dough into small bits and place onto nuts.
Melt oleo. Add brown sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon.
Heat just to dissolve.
Pour over bread.
Let rise to double the size.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool for just a couple of minutes, then invert onto plate at once.
Pull apart to eat.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Mix in rest of ingredients until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread and quick freeze on cookie sheet in freezer.
Store in freezer until ready to use.
Cook on cookie sheet at 425° for about 10 minutes or until bread is crispy and cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in long pan.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
In large bowl, beat eggs and egg whites until foamy.
Beat in milk, honey and vanilla.
Stir in bread cubes.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: maple dippers
directions: Combine sugar, butter, coconut, walnuts and milk.
Shape by teaspoons into small logs or patties.
Melt butterscotch and paraffin.
Add maple flavoring.
Using a fork, dip each log or patty into butterscotch mixture.
Yield: 125 pieces.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Fold in chocolate chips.
In a separate container, mix together flour, 4 cups sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Pat into large baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Bring to boil in saucepan over medium heat:
oleo, water, cocoa and Crisco.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into prepared 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup of pecans.
Mix together well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in the chopped pecans.
Chill good. Serve with crackers.

title: raisin surprise cookies
directions: Resift
flour
with
baking
soda
and salt into mixing bowl. In
another
bowl,
cream
sugars,
butter, vanilla and eggs.
Add 2
mixtures together and beat 1 minute on mixer or by hand
until blended and fluffy.
Stir in raisins, chocolate pieces and
nuts. Drop
from
teaspoon
in mounds
on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 4 dozen (3-inch) cookies.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Cream butter until very soft, gradually adding 1 cup of the sugar.
Stir in flavorings and stir thoroughly.
Add cream with remaining sugar, a	little at a time, until it is spreading consistency.

title: diabetic (no bake) cookies
directions: Cook margarine, milk and cocoa 1 minute.
Stir and add rest of ingredients.
Make into walnut-size balls.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, shortening, eggs, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combine remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
In a bowl, mash shrimp and add horseradish and lemon juice.
Add enough mayonnaise or Miracle Whip to make a spread.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mexican green chili
directions: Cut pork in bite-size pieces; dredge with flour and brown in oil.
Saute onion, garlic and add to pork.
Add tomato, water and green chilies.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with beans.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread thin layer of mixture over one side of boiled ham slice with cheese.
Roll up each slice in a roll.
Cut in 3 chunks.
Secure with toothpick.
Chill until firm.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Grease a 14 x 2-inch pizza pan.
On a flour-dusted surface, roll dough to 16 inch circle.
Press into bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of pan.
Sprinkle with 3 cups of cheese.
Crumble sausage over cheese.
Top with oregano, fennel seed, tomatoes, mushrooms and remaining cheese.
Place in a 500° oven; immediately reduce heat to 400°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove pizza when golden brown.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a two quart casserole dish; pour milk until macaroni is covered over.
Soak in fridge overnight or at least 5 hours.
Bake in a
350° oven for 50-60 minutes or until done.
May top with breadcrumbs and butter mixture.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Beat in whipped topping.
Bake pie crust.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom and let cool.
Put 1/2 of the mixture of topping and cream cheese in pie crust, then 1/2 of the blueberries and repeat.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugars until soft peaks form; beat in vanilla.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Pout into 2 (8-inch) waxed paper-lined cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool on racks for 10 minutes.
Turn out; remove paper.
Cool thoroughly.
Just before serving, put the layers together with whipped topping.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Simmer together celery and onion in oil.
Add seasoning, mushrooms and olives; bring to a boil.
Add 2 cups brown cooked rice and 1 cup peas.
Place in greased loaf pan and heat in oven. Do not overcook the peas.
Serves 6.

title: joe's pickled eggs
directions: Peel warm eggs and put in jar or Tupperware that has a lid. Pour liquid over eggs.
Cover and marinate 2 days before refrigeration.
Liquid may be reused by adding more hard-boiled eggs.

title: mayo biscuits
directions: Blend all 3 ingredients well.
Pour into greased muffin tins (2/3 full).
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 regular biscuits or 12 to 16 mini ones.

title: no fat no guilt carrot cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well; set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add flour mixture and blend well. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cake mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: layered pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and salt; beat until smooth. Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating until combined; spoon into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine 2 eggs, corn syrup, sugar and vanilla; beat well and pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix boiling water, melted shortening and sugar in bowl; cool. In another bowl, mix yeast and egg.
Stir flour into first mixture, then add second mixture.
Knead for 10 to 20 minutes, then let rest.
After rising, knead again.
Press out; cut into strips.
Dip each strip into melted butter before placing into a round cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.
Great to make the day before served!

title: fudgesicles
directions: Mix together with mixer for about 2 minutes.
Pour in freezer cups and freeze.
Serves 8.
Any flavor of pudding can be used.

title: dry mix for 4 batches of chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt and sugars) in bowl; cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator or freezer up to 6 months.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Put rice on bottom of pan.
Place chicken on top.
Pour over cranberries, onion soup mix and water.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally at 450° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: un-cheese mold
directions: Blend; cook 5 minutes.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: For each ice cream sandwich, press 1 slightly rounded tablespoonful of ice cream between 2 cookies.
Place in jelly roll pan. Freeze until firm.
Melt chips and shortening, stirring occasionally.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Dip half of each sandwich into chocolate.
Place in pan.
Freeze until firm. Store wrapped in plastic wrap.
Makes 15.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in bottom of dish.
Place the remaining ingredients on the lettuce, in the order given.
Spread salad dressing on top.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: cranberry percolator punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice, lemonade concentrate and apple cider into a 30-cup percolator.
Place spices in percolator basket. Perk through complete cycle.
Remove basket and stir in rum.
If desired, garnish with lemon wedges.

title: ga's pasta and beans
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large pot.
Add your oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook for about 1 to 2 minutes. Add beans with 2 cans of water.
Bring to a slow boil for about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and 1 can of water.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Finally, add your macaroni, cooking until macaroni is al dente.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and warm Italian bread.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat salad oil, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, in a greased Bundt pan.

title: tomato and bread salad
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Split baguette in half lengthwise.
Rub one half with garlic on cut side.
Brush with olive oil.
Cut garlic side in half again, lengthwise, then into 3/4-inch pieces. Place croutons on cookie sheet, crust side down and bake until golden, 30 minutes or more.

title: crackling bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a hot greased pan or skillet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for about 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut the ham, cheese, tomatoes, celery and pepper into bite-size pieces.
Add to the cold cooked spaghetti.
Add the Italian dressing and toss well.
Chill well before serving.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef.
In a large crock-pot, place Velveeta cheese and turn on high.
Begin melting cheese, then pour in salsa.
When melted smoothly, add ground beef.
Turn onto low and simmer for about 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Put onion soup in bottom of casserole dish.
Add meat.
Put soup and water over meat.
Cook 2 hours at 250° or all day in the crock-pot.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and remove seed from avocados.
Dice in small pieces. Sprinkle lemon juice over diced avocados, stirring to make sure all is covered to keep avocados from turning brown.
Add picante sauce and softened cream cheese, stirring until well mixed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli with salad dressing, sugar and vinegar; add cheese and bacon.
Toss and let set for 24 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop (set aside).
Pour oil into large mixing bowl; add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Gently fold in apples and pecans.
Spray tube pan with Pam; pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Remove from pan and drizzle on glaze.

title: stassi's marshmallows 'n fruit
directions: Mix instant pudding following package directions.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add fruit and mix well.
Add marshmallows. Chill and serve.

title: cobbler
directions: Press 1/2 of crumbs into a 9 x 13 pan. Add rhubarb mixture and put remaining crumbs over top. Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie monster delight
directions: Dip cookie into milk and place in 9 x 13 pan until the bottom is covered.
Put in thin layer of cool whip.
Continue layers (2-3) until pan is full.
Break 1-2 cookies and sprinkle on top. Chill overnight.
Makes a light and easy dessert.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use only an iron skillet.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together; marinade chicken pieces overnight or at least 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in marinade.
Makes 4 servings.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce, until well mixed.
Put mixture in loaf pan.
Cover with waxed paper and cook at High 15 to 16 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.
Drain off all juice.
Put meat loaf on serving plate and cover with tomato sauce.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and crumble corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, chocolate and
water. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet. Frost while warm.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Put in a microwave-safe dish.
Put 2 1/2 cups water and butter over potatoes.
Place in microwave for 9 minutes.
Check to see if potatoes are soft.
May need to microwave longer depending on watts of microwave.
When potatoes are soft, place 4 pieces of cheese over potatoes.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve..

title: macaroni and ham salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
While hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, seasonings and cheese.
Toss well.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate cake(diet recipe)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together first, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: mango (sugar-free) salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Put cream cheese in blender with mango juice and blend.
Add mango and blend smooth.
Mix with cool jello.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill. Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with almonds.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (batter includes everything except cinnamon, sugar and chocolate chips).
Pour 1/2 of cinnamon and sugar mixture on batter.
Sprinkle few chocolate chips.
Repeat whole process.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Place carrots, bacon and onion in baking dish, mix in salt and pepper.
Top with butter and brown sugar and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Toast macaroons for 4 minutes in 400° oven.
Place 1/2 of the macaroons on the bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer fruit in order given.
Top with remaining macaroons.
Refrigerate, covered, for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes, until mixture bubbles.
May be served with ice cream, pound cake or plain.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Make 2 days ahead.
Use for sandwiches or on crackers.

title: krazy korn
directions: Boil all ingredients (except nuts) together for 10 to 15 minutes until caramel colored.
Pour hot syrup over popped corn and mix well.
When cool, break into bite size pieces.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together in a punch bowl.
Add about a quart of water. Then put in 1 (32 ounce) can of pineapple juice.
Freeze half and then put back in when served.

title: zucchini crabcakes
directions: Use enough crumbs to thicken to properly form cakes.
Brown in oil until golden brown on both sides, turning only once.

title: sugar 'n spice cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the shortening, egg, sugar and molasses. Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Add to the shortening mixture.

When completely mixed, form into balls the size of walnuts. Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for approximately 8 minutes. Remove from oven and while still warm, cover completely with confectioners sugar.

title: frosted strawberry dessert
directions: Stir together the flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted butter. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
Remove and cool.

title: molasses bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups. In a medium bowl, combine cereal, milk and molasses.
Let stand until cereal is soft (1 to 2 minutes).
Add shortening and egg; beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Add cereal mixture all at once, stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full for 18 muffins or 3/4 full for 12 muffins.
Bake 14 to 18 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Immediately remove from pan.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pan and spread evenly.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.

title: seafood stuffing for fish
directions: Cook onion in butter or oleo over low flame until soft.
Add rest of ingredients.
Season to taste.
Stuff fish.

title: garlic basil dressing
directions: In a dressing decanter or jar, warm vinegar, then add sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed and shake well.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; cook and drain.
Set aside.
Add all other ingredients and heat through.
Add hamburger mixture; mix and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Spread butter (softened) in bottom of pie plate. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups coconut. Press in firmly and chill until firm.
Put eggs, sugar, juice, cheese and 1 cup coconut in blender. Blend well and pour into prepared pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's old-fashioned sugar creme pie
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine the sugar, half and half and whipping cream. Heat until mixture is warm, but not hot.
Add the flour a spoonful
at a time. When mixture is smooth, add nutmeg and ground cloves.
Heat over medium heat until mixture is smooth and thickened. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until set and slightly brown on top.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, egg yolks, lime juice and lemon juice; set aside.
Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into first mixture. Beat 3 remaining egg whites and gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Put into baked pie shell and bake at 350° until brown.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, and vanilla. Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in hot oven at 400 for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool on rack and chill in refrigerator.

title: "smilie face" pancakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together for pancake batter.
Cook pancakes on preheated griddle.
Add chocolate morsels when pouring the batter onto griddle.
When pancakes are done, take whipped cream and make a face on surface of pancake.
Garnish with chocolate chips.

title: mom's crispy chicken
directions: Clean and cut broiler size chickens in halves.
Place in bowl and completely cover with milk for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain, but do not wipe chickens.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat with cornflake crumbs.
In heavy frypan, heat oil (very hot).
Brown chicken quickly.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 35 to 50 minutes until tender in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Mix potatoes, milk, sugar, salt, 1/2 stick butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup milk.
Sprinkle on top (topping will be stiff).
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine 3 1/2 cups flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture alternately with lemon extract, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
(Batter will be thick.)
Dredge pecans and raisins in remaining 1/2 cup flour; stir into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove and let cool completely before serving.
Yield:
one 10-inch cake.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados; mix with 1 tablespoon lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning with mayonnaise.
Add a small amount of mayonnaise or sour cream to refried beans.
Use a large plate and spread layers in order:
refried beans, avocado, sour cream and seasoning mix, scallions, tomato, olives and cheese. Use Doritos to scoop and dip.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in pan the stuffing mix.
Add chicken broth to moisten well.
Mix other ingredients together. Spread on top of stuffing and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or top browns good.

title: spinach and dandelion soup
directions: To the stock, add the dandelion greens and spinach.
Add green onions, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until greens are tender. Serve in bowls with nutmeg and eggs as garnish.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix and stir constantly until thick.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water to Jell-O and 1 cup pineapple juice.
Let gel, not solid.
Whip in cream cheese and Cool Whip. Fold in pineapple and celery.
Chill and serve.

title: oriental pork roast
directions: Rub roast with 5-spice powder.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven or large heavy skillet, over medium-high, brown meat on all sides in oil.
Transfer meat to slow cooker.
In remaining oil in Dutch oven, saute onions, sesame seed and garlic for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 cups water, soy sauce and bouillon granules. Stir to loosen browned bits from bottom.
Pour mixture over roast in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 4 1/2 to 5 hours or on low for 9 to 10 hours or until tender.
Move meat to platter. Skim fat from broth.
Pour broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, stir 1/3 cup cold water and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir until thickened.
Spoon over carved roast.

title: sticky buns #1
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 30 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Melt 1/4 stick butter in large skillet.
Pour pancake mixture into skillet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into sections.
Remove.
Serve.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and pour syrup over pancake.

title: rhubarb salad("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and salt in saucepan and cook over low heat until tender.
Do not stir or add water as rhubarb makes its own juice.
Pieces should stay whole.
Then bring mixture quickly to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately and add 2 packages of jello.
Stir carefully to dissolve.
Add cold water, celery and lemon juice.
Chill until very thick.
Makes about 5 (1/2 cup) molds.

title: california slim dip
directions: Place skim milk and cottage cheese in blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy, about 4 minutes.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 2 cups.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry shrimp in oil in deep frying pan for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add eggs, salt and pepper. Fry over medium for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add the rice and soy sauce.
Fry 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Garnish with chopped scallions. Serves 6.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Place sugar, shortening, lemon juice, lemon peel, vanilla and lemon extract in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to shortening mixture. Beat at low speed just until blended.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini until barely tender.
Add cubed cheese to drained zucchini.
Mix together 2 eggs, flour, milk, baking powder, salt and parsley flakes.
Pour mixture over zucchini and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Place flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in mixing bowl. Cut the butter into dry ingredients with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Stir in currants and milk until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured surface and pat into 1/2-inch thickness.
Place on baking sheet and, cutting almost to bottom, score into 12 wedges with a knife.
If desired, brush with milk or sprinkle lightly with cinnamon-sugar. Bake in preheated 400° oven until browned, about 15 minutes. Serve warm with butter, honey or preserves.

title: brittle cookies
directions: You will need a cookie sheet.

title: spinach dip in rye bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bread.
Cut out center of one loaf of bread.
Put dip in center.
Cut second loaf in cubes and put around first loaf to dip in it.
Make dip night before; put dip in bread right before serving.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aggie's hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; cook until mixture becomes a soft ball in cold water.
Take off heat and beat egg whites into mixture.

title: angel food cake frosting
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in kettle on the stove and cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
After thickened, take off stove and add oleo and vanilla.
Stir into mixture and put on cooled angel food cake.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Dissolve jello in liquid.
Let sit until thick but do not refrigerate.
Put berries in pie shell.
Let sit 4 to 6 hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: linda's cheese ball
directions: Squeeze all of juice from pineapple.
Mix with cream cheese. Combine other ingredients (reserving 1 cup pecans) and mix with cheese.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream date dreams
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add egg and mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to shortening alternately with sour cream.
Stir in dates.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Top each with walnut half. Bake at 400° for ten minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: steak supper special
directions: On wax paper, mix flour and salt; coat steaks in hot oil. Cook steaks until brown on both sides, about 4 minutes.
Place steaks on a slice of bread.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and chiles in large pan; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Press 5 biscuits over bottom of ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and 1 cup flour as for a pie crust.
Press in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice, 2 Tbsp. flour and baking powder together and spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with powdered sugar and lemon juice.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauce for baked ham
directions: Combine all ingredients & bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute. Spread on ham the last half hour of baking (400 degrees).

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add soup, sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Cover bottom with 1/2 the bread crumbs.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with rest of bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: pickled okra
directions: Divide okra into 5 pint jars.
Leave short stem (stem down in first layer, then vice-versa).
Divide dill, garlic, peppers and alum amount jars.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal jars.
Allow to pickle at least 2 weeks before serving.

title: macaroon bars
directions: Mix all together and put half of dough into jelly roll pan. Then mix one box of macaroon mix with 3/4 cup of water and spread on mixture in pan.
Cover with rest of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla,
blending
thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and
salt;
add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add bananas and pecans,
mixing
until
well blended.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Soften cream and Bleu cheeses at room temperature.
Add Worcestershire sauce and dash each of onion and garlic powder. Mix well.
Shape into ball; roll into walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy banana bread
directions: With mixer, cream shortening and granulated sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add bananas.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Add nuts. Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy 4 step dessert
directions: Spread in a 9 x 12-inch flat Pyrex dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Make a dough of the potatoes, flour, egg, salt, pepper and lard.
Knead well and form dough into dumplings the size of eggs. Cook in large pan of boiling salted water for about 20 minutes or until fluffy and cooked through.
Drain in colander and keep warm. Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan; crumble.
Mix bacon crumbles and green onions together.
Turn dumplings into bacon and onion mix until coated.
Serve topped with cottage cheese.

title: rosy red punch
directions: Mix together and stir to blend.
Add ice, if desired.
Takes five minutes.
Serves 40.

title: soup from a can
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients, then remaining ingredients; simmer together.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine over low heat.
Add milk and cocoa. Blend well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking dish.
Combine catsup, water and brown sugar and pour over chops.
Thinly slice lemon and place one slice on top of each pork chop.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream margarine and the sugars in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg, oil, oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, soda and vanilla.
Shape by teaspoon into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: orange & pineapple congealed salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Drain pineapple.
Mix with Jell-O and congeal.
Sprinkle nuts on congealed mixture.
Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip and mix with cream cheese.
Spread over nuts.
In small boiler beat eggs, sugar, flour and juice.
Cook until thick.
Cover and cool.
Spread over Dream Whip.
This makes a big 9 x 13 dish.
Hint:
make Jell-O at night and finish the next morning.

title: hot and sour chicken
directions: Cook a whole chicken for a short period of time.
Let cool. Remove skin and bones.
Slice chicken.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place drained pineapple, cranberries, nuts, celery and sugar in a large bowl; let stand 1 hour.
Prepare jello per box instructions.
When it starts to jell, add fruit ingredients. Pour into 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and refrigerate.

title: mock lemon pie
directions: Mix together sugar,
egg yolks, vinegar and cornstarch. Add boiling water.
Cook
like	custard
(in a double boiler). Add lemon extract and cool.
Put
beaten
egg
whites
on top. Place in a 350° oven for 15 minutes to brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat fruit.
Melt oleo in a large casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and beat until mixed. Pour into butter dish and stir until blended with oleo.
Pour hot fruit evenly over batter. Bake at 350° until dough rises to top and browns about 1 hour.
Blackberries may be used instead of peaches.

title: miracle icing
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high flame and cook for 3 minutes.
Place unbeaten egg whites and cream of tartar in small mixer bowl.
Turn switch to fast and immediately add hot syrup.
Continue to beat for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Frosts a 2-layer cake (generously).
I frosted a loaf cake and a 2-layer cake.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Beat together until lemon colored the yolks of eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and grated rind.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Let cool.
Add egg whites beaten stiff into which is stirred 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add whipped cream.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Spread coconut evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Prepare cake mix, following package directions for original recipe.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Heat soups, mushrooms, water.
Reserve 1 cup; add rice.
Pour in baking dish; lay chicken on top, cover with reserved 1 cup of soup mixture.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mincemeat salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in orange juice.
Cool slightly.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in small skillet until golden brown.
Cook, covered, until tender.
Stir in tomato juice and tomato paste.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef with seasoning in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Layer hot rice and ground beef mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: human puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Put cereal into a large bowl.
Pour mixture over cereal and mix well. Pour some powdered sugar in the bottom of a double grocery bag. Add some of the cereal mixture, then more powdered sugar and shake well.
Keep alternating until all are added.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside for topping.
To remaining mixture, add milk and baking powder.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crumb topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine beef, tomatoes, water, chili powder, green pepper and onion in a large saucepan. Bring to
boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan with 1/3 of the tortillas.
Top with 1/3 of the sauce and 1/3 of the cheese. Repeat with the remaining ingredients, making 2 more layers but reserving the remaining 1/3 cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top of the casserole.
Serve with salsa, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pie (from mama)
directions: Line a deep pie pan with a rich pie crust and bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 13x9-inch pan to coat pan well.
Mix the margarine and other ingredients except cheese in pan, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 350° for 30 - 45 minutes until brown.

title: fruited oatmeal drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add bananas.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Stir in oats.
Add raisins, nuts and cherries.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: polish sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients with pork.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup cold water slowly, about 1/4 cup at a time.
Mix well, then add another 1/4 cup, mixing until the 1 cup is used up.
(If the meat clings to your hands, add still another 1/4 cup water.)
When cutting the pork butt, do not remove the fat.
Attach funnel to mixer.
Keep funnel wet for casings to slide on.
Tie off ends.
When cooking, use just enough water to cover sausage.
Simmer; boil on low flame and cook about 1/2 hour.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cook the raisins and water until 1 cup liquid remains.
Cool. Add the baking soda to the 1 cup liquid.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves alternately with raisin liquid.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: flexible fruit salad
directions: Choose several fruits in season from these: fresh pineapple, grapes, bananas, cherries, apples, oranges, peaches, nectarines, melon, blueberries, etc.
Prepare 6 to 8 cups by doing necessary peeling, pitting, coring or seeding.
Slice or cube into a large bowl.
Carefully stir in one 8 ounce container of yogurt and 1/4 cup sunflower seeds.
Chill.

title: macaroni shells
directions: Boil shells and drain; brown onions and peppers in oleo.
Toss together tomato soup, mushroom soup, milk and cheese; pour over shells and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Beat cream cheese and margarine at medium speed for 2 minutes or until mixture is creamy. Gradually add flour, beating at low speed until blended. Spoon dough into miniature muffin pans, filling two-thirds full, or refrigerate dough up to 3 days. Bake for 17 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately. Makes 2 dozen.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix in large bowl the sugar, peanut butter and softened butter. Mix well. Make into small balls. Place in freezer for awhile.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash river rice; let water come to a boil and add rice.
Bring back to a boil; cook down until rice is dry.
Add milk, sugar, egg yolks and nutmeg.
Cook until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, then add 2 teaspoons sugar at a time.
Continue beating after each addition.
Spread on pudding and bake in a 350° oven until it browns good.

title: busy day baked beans
directions: Distribute bread crumbs in dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese evenly over bread.
Snip smoked ham with scissors over cheese. Beat eggs lightly and add mustard and milk; stir to blend.
Pour this mixture in casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or the night before. Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: In 2 1/2-quart pot, Teflon or spray with Pam, place beef in pot.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook until meat changes color.
Add onions, celery and green pepper; mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and liquid and all seasonings, mixing well.
Bring to a boil; cover and turn heat low and simmer gently for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans and beef broth.
Continue cooking over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together and spread in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan; simmer until thick.

title: easy butter crunch candy
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and almonds.
Cook over high flame, stirring constantly, until mix is golden brown, 5 to 10 minutes. Spread in 8 x 10-inch buttered pan.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff, adding 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Set aside.
Cream butter.
Add rest of sugar, then beat well.
Add yolks, about 2 at a time; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in large (10-inch) tube pan which has been greased and floured on bottom only at 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours until tester comes out clean.
Cool right side up on rack.

title: zucchini treat
directions: Wash and cut zucchini in quarters and cook in boiling slightly salted water until done.
Don't over cook.
Drain well, let cool, cut in small pieces and slightly squeeze out excess water.
Place in a large bowl, add beaten eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix very well.
Oil bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle some bread crumbs and smooth out.
Spread mixture on crumbs.
Sprinkle a few more crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top of mixture and bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes or until brown on top.
Can be served warm or can be cut in 2-inch squares when cold and served as hors d'oeuvres.

title: lamb kabobs
directions: Cut up lamb into cubes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; cool.
Roll out the graham crackers and mix with margarine and powdered sugar.
Use most of the cracker mixture to line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, cream together sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix with cold jello.
Whip chilled evaporated milk until stiff.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Pare
and
slice
or dice the potatoes.
Peel and slice the onions.
Cook these vegetables in a saucepan with a small amount of	water
so
that the water will be used up when the vegetables are just tender.
Add the tuna, milk, salt, pepper and
butter. Heat
slowly.
Taste
for
further seasoning, if desired.

title: pork roast with rosemary crust
directions: Make small slits in the meat and tuck pieces of garlic and rosemary into the pork.
Brush the meat all over with olive oil and roast in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
After you have mixed well, form mixture into a log shape by pressing mixture together until dough sticks.
Lay cheese log on a piece of wax paper wrap. Put into refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Place 1/4-inch thick sliced cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 400° for about 6 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan after you take out of oven.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut wings in 3 pieces; discard end piece of wings.
Use a deep fryer with Puritan oil.
Cook at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: whipped nonfat milk
directions: Place ice water and lemon juice in small deep bowl.
Sprinkle dry milk powder on top.
Beat until stiff enough to hold soft peaks with a rotary beater (about 15 minutes) or use an electric beater.
Fold in sugar substitute.
Makes 1 cup.

title: no-bake lemon pie(low-carb)
directions: Cream cheese must be at room temperature. Put cream cheese in medium-size bowl and beat with mixer on medium speed. Add lemon juice and Splenda.
(Start with 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1 teaspoon Splenda. Go from this point to determine how tart or sweet you want your pie, mixing and tasting after each addition.)

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: jean hardin's salad
directions: Heat pineapple, add jello and let cool.
Mix with buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Let set until firm.
Good for diabetics.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chocolate crust. Chill and serve.

title: cherry red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve after chilling.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix in microwave bowl the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Heat on High for 3 minutes.
(The chips will look glossy.) Stir in peanuts.
Stir until completely coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put corn in baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and then spread over corn.
Sprinkle cheese over that.
Mix butter and cracker crumbs and spread over that.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in raisins.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add liquid to dry ingredients; mix until moistened. Turn into greased loaf pan (5 1/4 x 9 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: mama's peanut butter candy
directions: Put milk and brown sugar in pan; heat to boil.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil the water, margarine and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Remove form heat. Add the flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix well and add the eggs and sour cream. Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet (18 x 12 x 1-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tumbleweed
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Can be frozen and eaten as a soft ice cream or can be poured from blender into a glass and enjoyed immediately.

title: orange jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-o in hot water. Add orange juice, mandarin oranges, and pineapple. Chill until firm. Whip vanilla pudding mix with milk. Fold in cool whip. Add nuts. Spread over chilled Jell-o. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package and set aside.
Mix rice and Cheez Whiz.
Melt margarine and saute onion and celery, then add soup.
Remove from heat.
Add to rice mixture and add broccoli, then mix all ingredients well and pour in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine	in
a
saucepan.
Combine margarine and brown sugar in a	mixing	bowl.
Stir and let cool 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at
a
time,
beating after each.
Add flour and stir until completely	moistened.
Add
pecans
and chocolate chips.
Stir. Pour mixture in greased and floured 8 x 14-inch glass pan.	Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat rice balls
directions: Combine rice (right from the box) with the beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of tomato sauce; mix lightly.
Shape into balls; place in skillet.
Add sugar and
water to the remaining tomato sauce.
Pour sauce over meat balls in skillet.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: orange artichoke layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order and drizzle with olive oil. Great for Christmas Eve dinner.

title: kahlua liquor
directions: Boil the instant coffee and 2 5/8 cups boiling water; set aside to cool.
Boil the sugar and 5 cups water for 5 minutes, then cool.
Mix together, then add the vanilla and vodka.
Mix all together; pour into 4 fifth size bottles and seal.
This liquor may not be refrigerated and will keep.
Makes 4 1/2 fifths.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake in moderate oven (300° to 350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix enough milk for a stiff batter. Drop by teaspoon in hot fat until brown.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together in a medium bowl, set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and zucchini.
Mix with electric mixer or by hand until will blended, about 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brownies test done.
Cut into pieces.

title: grandmother's cookies
directions: Cream
together oleo, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in flour, salt, soda,
oatmeal and pecans.
Mix well, and bake 10 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and bake in pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: mexican cornbread(hot)
directions: Combine cornbread mix in a large bowl; add milk and stir.
Add other ingredients in given order.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° about 35 minutes.

title: artichoke souffle
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of artichokes into frypan.
Discard other jar's marinade.

Add onion and garlic to pan and saute. Beat eggs with fork. Add crumbs. Stir in cheese, parsley, seasonings, artichokes and sauteed mixture. Bake in greased 9 x 11-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°. Set 10 minutes before cutting. Can be served cold or hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix by directions on box.
Place half of stuffing mix in the bottom of 2 liter casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients together until mixed well.
Pour mixture over stuffing and cover with other half of remaining stuffing mix. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: easy pot roast with gravy
directions: Cook
roast in crock-pot with water and gravy mix until slightly
tender.
Add
salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce, as desired.
Add chopped vegetables and cook until tender.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in oven, then put in crock to keep warm.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in refrigeratable bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar, milk and syrup until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, powdered sugar and red food coloring.
Beat until smooth.
Drop into patties on wax paper to cool.

title: a b c cheese ball
directions: Mix all.
Form mixture into a ball.
Serve with crackers and fresh cut vegetables.

title: cinnamon roll
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Mix milk and 3 cups warm water together; add to flour.
Mix eggs and Crisco, then add yeast mixture.
Let stand until doubled, then punch down.
Let it rise again.
Make 4 even balls to roll.
Combine 3 cups sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in butter, then sugar-cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: daddy lutz's oyster dressing
directions: In black skillet fry onions in a little oil.
In bowl mix other seasonings, chopped oysters and juice, crumbled French bread, eggs, salt and pepper.
Fry in a little oil skilletfuls of this mixture until it becomes dry.
Put broth and all of the fried down oysters and seasonings, baked giblets and neck in a shallow baking pan.
Bake until thick gravy consistency.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Thaw frog legs.
If frozen, separate into individual legs. In shallow dish, combine flour, salt and ground red pepper.

Dip frog legs into flour mixture, a few at a time, to coat thoroughly. In a saucepan or deep fat fryer, heat about 2-inches of cooking oil to 375°. Fry coated frog legs, a few at a time, in deep hot fat about 2 minutes or until done.
Keep warm in a 325° oven while frying the remainder.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese platter
directions: Arrange attractively on a large platter or cutting board and serve with sliced pears and apples, clusters of green and red grapes and whole strawberries.
Fresh French bread and butter accompany this finale to a French meal.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together.
Melt butter or margarine and combine milk, eggs, vanilla, bananas and nuts together along with melted butter to the dry ingredients.
Pour into a deep baking pan and bake until top is golden brown.
Insert a toothpick to insure cake is done.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream
1 1/2 cups sugar with margarine. Add eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, salt and baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients to egg mixture.
Chill.
Form into balls and roll them in nutmeg mixed with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: food for the gods
directions: Mix baking powder and sugar;
add dates, nuts, yolks of eggs and crumbs.
Then add beaten whites.
Line bottom of long pan with greased
paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yummy with whipped cream on top.

title: dilly dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: never fail fluffy biscuits
directions: Sift together into a bowl:
flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Add shortening.
Cut in with pastry blender until the mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Add milk all at once.
Stir just enough to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board.
Knead lightly for 30 seconds.
Roll out to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut with a floured 2-inch round cutter. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: english pancakes
directions: Put flour in a mixing bowl and add beaten egg.
Mix in the egg and add milk until you have a liquid batter.
Make sure you have no lumps.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; put in sheet pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix (dry) over top of pumpkin mix.
Add the chopped pecans over cake mix.
Melt the margarine; spoon over pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grilled southwest burgers
directions: Prepare medium-hot fire in covered charcoal or gas grill. Beat egg, then add meat, bread crumbs, milk, chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and cayenne in mixing bowl.
Use your hands to mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into 6 patties about 1/2-inch thick. Grill patties, turning once, until well browned on outside and no longer pink in center about 15 to 17 minutes.
Top each patty with 1 slice cheese and place rolls, cut side down on grill.
Cook about 30 seconds to melt cheese and lightly toast rolls.
Garnish burger with salsa, or taco sauce and shredded lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with condensed milk.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla. Spread into waxed paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off waxed paper and cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: First do: 2 c. raisins with 1 c. water. Boil 5 minutes or until liquid is decreased to 1/2 c. and cool. Then cream shortening. Add sugar and blend well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla, nuts and cooled raisins. Mix. Add dry ingredients and blend well. Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 400 degrees 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: quick chili
directions: In a big saucepan, saute onion, garlic and green pepper in butter for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beef and saute for 1 minute (until beef is brown) the spoon out excess fat.
Add chili powder, water, tomatoes, bay leaf, salt, cumin and cayenne. Bring to boil.
Add beans and simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick energy pick-ups
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl. Shape teaspoons of the mixture into 1 inch balls.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs until coated.
Arrange balls on ungreased cookie sheet and refrigerate 20 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange ice
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and freeze.

title: fried bananas
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
