Add eggs, milk and oil.
If mixture becomes too thick, add 1 tablespoon milk.
Cut bananas into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Dip into Tempura batter and fry quickly in very hot oil until golden brown.
Blot on paper towels and serve while hot.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water to dissolve.
Stir together flour and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add yeast mixture and oil.
Stir until rough dough forms.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Shape into ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to coat.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Punch down and divide into two parts.
(Dough may be frozen at this point, up to 2 months.) Roll out dough to fit pizza pan and let rise in pan 15 minutes. Bake crust at 450° for 10 minutes.
Add toppings and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet until it loses its redness. Remove from skillet and cook macaroni, onion and green pepper in meat fat until macaroni is yellow.

Return meat to skillet along with tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit taste (you may add additional water, if needed).

title: the best spaghetti sauce
directions: Take onions and chop them up small.
Cover the bottom of the frying pan with olive oil.
Take ground beef and add with the onions in the frying pan.
The stove should be on low heat.
Add any seasonings you would like and mix those with the hamburger and onions.
Mix well.
When the hamburger is cooked, add Prego sauce with the onions and hamburger.
Mix all together until the sauce is heated and mixed properly with the hamburger and onions. Remove from frying pan and it is ready to serve, or you can save it to serve later.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
In a large bowl cream together the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place chicken breasts on cutting board and pound lightly with side of heavy knife or cleaver until about 1/4-inch thick. Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then crumbs.
Heat oil until very hot in a large skillet.
Quickly brown chicken on both sides; remove to a shallow baking dish. Pour excess oil from skillet.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add chilies and 1 package onion soup mix. Set aside to cool.

title: cooked buttercream frosting
directions: Microwave:
In small bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon of water, 3 tablespoons of the sugar and the yolk.
Cook, stirring every 15 seconds, until bubbles, about 45 seconds to 1 minute. Set aside.
Allow to cool about 15 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix.
Roll into balls and roll into sugar.

title: beef noodle vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in noodles and vegetables.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.

title: white bean chili
directions: Heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add onions and saute.
Stir in garlic, chilies and spices.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add cooked beans and chicken stock.
Reduce heat and cook until seasonings mingle.
Add chicken and 1 cup of cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Ladle into bowls and top with remaining cheese, sour cream and salsa.

title: caramel pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half into pie crust.
Drizzle with half of caramel topping.
Sprinkle half of coconut and pecans over caramel.
Repeat layers.
Chill or freeze until ready to serve.
Can be doubled for a crowd.
Can be made ahead of time and stored in freezer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Pound veal and season with salt and pepper. Brown veal in either olive oil or margarine (2 tablespoons).
Combine tomatoes, tomato paste, green pepper, mushrooms and seasonings. Stir until tomatoes are broken up.
Add to veal in skillet. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Uncover and simmer 30 more minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, dill weed, lemon juice, onion and garlic salt and chill one hour.
Chip beef in blender and mix with other ingredients.
Cut rectangle out of long bread loaf.
Fill bread cavity with dip.
Cut rectangle part of bread in small squares and place around and on loaf, then serve.

title: pork chops and noodles
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix together mushrooms, celery soup, water and thyme and add to pork chops.
Add onions and carrots.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve over wide cooked noodles.

title: italian food
directions: From Lewisville go west on 1171; turn south on 2499.
Go approximately 1 block and turn right into Salerno's Restaurant.
If you are coming from another direction area call 539-9534 and get directions.
The address is 3407 Long Prairie Road, Flower Mound. Tell them Dan sent you and they will let you order anything on the menu at the regular price.

title: fruit cake
directions: Leave nuts and fruits whole.
Sift sugar, salt, flour and baking powder.
Add sifted ingredients to fruit.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Add to mix and mix well.
Recipe is for 3 loaf pans. Grease and line loaf pans with wax paper.
Grease paper and fill. Pack down.
Place a pan of water in oven while baking.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Remove wax paper while warm.
Cool.
Freeze or refrigerate cake in Saran, then foil.

title: oreo cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Crush 3/4 package of Oreos.
Mix with butter.
Press into bottom of 2-quart glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients (except Oreos).
Blend.
Pour half the mixture onto crust.
Break remaining Oreos into pieces and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Pour remaining mixture on top. Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 200°.
Bake 45 minutes. Turn off oven.
With door slightly ajar, allow to cool for 2 hours.

title: creamy egg roll ala jeanne
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine the chop suey vegetables, crab meat, Miracle Whip and soy sauce.
Mix lightly.
For each egg roll, spoon approximately 1/4 mixture into the center of each wrapper.
Moisten edges of wrapper lightly with water.
Fold one corner over filling, then the opposite corner, then roll over remaining corner to seal.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, until crisp and golden brown.
Make and bake right away.
Do not them sit around or they will get soggy!
Serve with sweet and sour or mustard.
Yum!
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Add to the egg yellows the flour, sugar, pumpkin and milk.
Mix together, then add browned butter and vanilla.
Mix again.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour into pie shell.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes.
Protect edge of crust with aluminum foil.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini; cut into thin slices.
Peel onions; slice thin. Cover vegetables with water, adding the 1/4 cup salt; let stand for 2 hours, then drain well.
In saucepan, combine the vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed; bring to a boil.
Pour over drained vegetables.
Let stand two hours.
Return to heat.
Bring to boil and cook for five minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Seal tightly.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix melted butter or oleo, chopped nuts, cake mix and 1 egg together.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Pour this mixture over other mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add all ingredients to macaroni and mix well.

title: potato and blue cheese salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Drain. Add to dressing and toss.

title: pineapple-mango salsa
directions: Toss together all ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes. Serve with grilled seafood or tortilla chips. Makes 6 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add oil, honey and vanilla. Bake at 200° to 250° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Brown beef, onions and green pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken steak(chinese)
directions: Wash, then dry chicken legs with paper towels.
Cut the chicken legs at the joint to yield 8 pieces.
Debone and discard the skins.
Marinate chicken pieces in a bowl with cornstarch, soy sauce, sherry, salt, sugar and garlic.
Set aside for 30 minutes or overnight.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven at 320°.
Bake 25 minutes or until done.
Nuts are optional.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in buttered pan or dish.
Place cheese on top. Combine soup, wine and chicken stock in a pan.
Stir well and heat.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken. Drizzle butter over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hash browns in casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Just before placing in oven, put crushed potato chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or turn down to 325° for last 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar (let cool).
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir.
Add flour and stir, then add chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream first five ingredients together and gradually add flour.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mince onion and parsley, either by hand or with food processor.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients; hand roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Use Teflon frying pan.
Spray with Pam; cook at low heat until brown on all sides.
Can bake with Pam also.

title: tangy molded cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and chill to soft jelly.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple, including juice and fruit, chopped walnuts, horseradish and mayonnaise.
Mix well and mold.

title: international mocha mix
directions: Mix in a large container.
Put in jars to give as gifts. Attach bow and instructions to add 1/3 cup dry mix to 1 cup boiling water for a delicious hot drink.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Beat remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk, cake mix and margarine in bowl.
Pour half the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Wrap 1 strip of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place side by side in baking dish that has been covered with chopped beef. Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Do not salt.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: "canned biscuits" cinnamon roll ring
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and shake in 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar mixture.
Place half of the biscuits into ungreased Bundt cake pan.
Mix remainder of sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Pour half of this mixture over biscuits. Layer remaining biscuits and syrup and top with nuts.
Bake on
medium heat for 1 hour or until done.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll small amount with fingers into strawberry shape.
Roll in red crystal sugar.
Dip stem end in green crystal sugar.
Insert whole clove for stem.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: josephinas
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, mix the chiles, butter, mayonnaise and cheese until well blended.
Slice the French bread into thin slices and spread amply with the cheese mixture, making sure to completely cover the bread.
Place the bread slices on an ungreased cookie sheet in a preheated broiler and broil about 5 to 10 minutes until the spread is bubbly.
Serve on a large serving plate garnished with parsley sprigs.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, cream cheese and milk.
Mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake by box directions.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or 1 (12 x 16-inch) pan that have been greased and floured.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix 1 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup sugar; bring to a boil.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved over low heat.
Add coconut and pour over hot cake.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Blend cream of celery soup with water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture.
Combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Brown meatballs in shortening.
Add remaining soup mixture and the pickle.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until thick and lemony.
Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add milk and vanilla.
Carefully fold dry ingredients into egg mixture by hand.
Blend well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken breast and cut in half to make 8 pieces.
Place breast in a greased pan.
Cover each piece of chicken with a slice of cheese.
Mix a can of cream of chicken soup with a can of cream of celery soup and pour over top of cheese.
Cover all with Stove Top stuffing then pour 1/2 cup of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: bronco bread
directions: Combine butter, water, orange juice and rind in a bowl.
Add egg; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; fold in blueberries by hand. Bake at 325° in greased 9 x 15-inch baking pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Freezes well.

title: beef pot roast and vegetables
directions: Roll roast in 1/2 cup flour, pepper and 2 teaspoons salt. Brown roast slowly in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Reduce heat to 250°. Add 1/2 cup water and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as needed to prevent sticking. Add onions and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer until tender. Remove.

title: fluffy fruit dressing(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and orange juice with rotary beater. Stir in salad dressing and vanilla.

title: coconut chiffon dessert
directions: Bring juice and 7-Up to a boil.
Add marshmallows until dissolved; cool until thickened (you may refrigerate if necessary).
Add Cool Whip to cooled mix.
Alternate with cake, mixture and top with coconut.

title: chuck wagon carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan bring 3/4 cup water to a boil.
Add carrots.
Cover; cook over medium heat until carrots are crisply tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain, set aside.
In same saucepan melt butter.
Stir in carrots.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through (5 to 7 minutes).
Yields 4 servings.

title: instant cocoa with marshmallows
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Give mix with the recipe for Hot Cocoa.
Yields 16 cups of mix, enough for 32 servings.

title: praline sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and butter; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and cool.
When lukewarm, add milk.
Store in jar.
Keeps long time!

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage and cook about 10 minutes, until barely tender.
In a buttered baking dish, put a layer of cabbage.
Then, put slices of cheese and crumbled crackers.
Repeat layers until gone.
Pour milk over; cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken-chipped beef bake
directions: Roll chicken breasts and wrap 1 strip bacon around each and pin with toothpick.
Place dried beef flat in bottom of 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place rolled chicken on dried beef.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove and add over top sour cream and mushroom soup (which is mixed together).
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Separate mushrooms, cap and stem.
Rinse and pat dry.
Combine salt and pepper with flour.
First put mushrooms in flour.
Roll in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towel.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well and pour in a baking dish.
In a skillet melt 1 stick oleo.
Crumble 1 package white crackers; pour in oleo and mix. Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together and shape into small balls. Put in fridge for a few minutes.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls in the melted chocolate and set on wax paper.
Put in fridge for a few minutes to set chocolate.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook sausage and drain well. Fry bacon, drain and crumble. Mix all.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook onions, tomatoes and green peppers to pieces.
Cook all for 4 hours on stove.
You can add cheese with this, but I like crackers with it best of all.
I think you would like this.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: white ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet and bring to a simmer; turn off heat.
(Enough for 1 1/2 pound ham.)

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk.
Turn out on floured board; knead 10 times. Roll out to 12 x 8 x 1/2-inch.
Cut into strips (pizza cutter works great).
Dip sticks into melted margarine and lay them in pan close together.
Sprinkle with one of the toppings:
garlic salt and dry cheese or grated cheese or cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and onion in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Take the salt, pepper, soup and milk mixture and pour over the potatoes.
Dot with butter and sprinkle it with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.

title: gramma behr chocolate cake
directions: Cut up 4 ounces bitter chocolate and 1/2 cup shortening in bowl; add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until melted.
Add 2 cups sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 cups flour, sifted with 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda.
Add to first mixture, then add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake in 8-inch or 9-inch pans.
For 8-inch bake 25 minutes at 350°; for 9-inch bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Depending on your stove, test the cake before taking out of oven.
Use a wooden toothpick.
It's done if the toothpick comes out cleanly.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in saucepan, making sure not to burn the bottom.
Add the corn flakes to them and mix.
When the corn flakes are completely covered, drop in tablespoon-sized balls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until hard, approximately 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: meatballs in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients but the soup and 1/3 can milk.
Shape into balls and brown in butter 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot pasta salad
directions: In a small bowl combine vinegar, oil and salt.
Set aside. Spray 12-inch nonstick skillet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Heat skillet over medium heat.
Add pepper, onion and poppy seed.
Cook for 4 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add linguine and tomato.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until hot, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar mixture.
Toss to combine. Serve hot.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients except jelly, just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups only 1/2 full.
Drop 1 teaspoon jelly in center of each and add batter to fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan. Yields 12 muffins.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a slightly greased crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: three fruit drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Process until frothy.
Serve chilled.
Yields 4 cups.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly and then place in large bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients in another bowl or container and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over the beans and mix gently to coat all of the beans.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Salad may be kept up to 2 weeks, if refrigerated.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together while potatoes are warm.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding gradually 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set for two hours in refrigerator. Garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and fruit cocktail, beat with dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
In another bowl, mix coconut, sugar and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate lovers delight cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to box directions.
Once cooked, poke holes with a wooden spoon in hot cake.
Pour milk over cake then hot fudge and caramel sauce.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip and sprinkle Heath crunch on top.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in microwave.
Drain well.
Cream soup, cheese and egg yolks until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Combine spinach, creamed mixture and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and top with French fried onion rings.
Bake additional 20 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle nuts on top if desired.

title: meltaway butterfingers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and salt.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add walnuts and vanilla; mix with hands to form a smooth dough.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute in 1/4 cup butter, stirring often, for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add just enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 2 cups milk (cold). Add to vegetables, stirring slowly.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together with electric mixer.
Pour batter into a greased lightly floured 9 x 13 pan.

title: surprise meringue kisses
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar, and, if desired, peppermint extract until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 1 1/2-inches apart onto a highly greased cookie sheet.
Press chocolate kiss into each cookie.
With a knife or narrow spatula, bring meringue up and over candy and swirl the top.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Immediately remove and cool. Makes about 44.

title: no fat bean dip
directions: Mix all together and cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with large corn chips.
Keeps well for a couple weeks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop beef, onions and water chestnuts up fine and mix all other ingredients together.
Chill overnight and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: lemon bar cookies
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry
cutter.
Press in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15	minutes.
Combine eggs, 1 cup sugar, grated lemon rind and lemon
juice; beat well.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon
baking
powder;
stir
well.
Pour
over	baked crust. Bake at
for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cool.
Cut	into
1/2-inch
square
bars.
Store
in airtight container.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Defrost raspberries, strain and reserve juice.
Mix jello and crushed pineapple with liquid.
Add raspberries.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into a 10-inch mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: punch
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes.

title: play-doh for children
directions: Bring water,
salt
and
food coloring to a boil.
Add vegetable oil and alum.
Pour
mixture into flour.
Mix and knead. This isn't as sticky as store
bought
play-doh and can be used many times if kept in covered jar when not in use.

title: christmas salad
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and stir in applesauce.
Chill until firm in a ringed mold (8-inch).
Serve with sour cream.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, hard-boiled eggs, mushrooms and almonds with soup until gone in casserole dish. Crumble Cheez-Its on top. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion, carrots and celery in margarine.
Add chicken broth and water.
Stir in lentils and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: orange breakfast bread pudding
directions: Place bread slices in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, turning once.
Cool on a wire rack. Cut into cubes; set aside. Lightly coat six 6-ounce custard cups with cooking spray.
Divide bread cubes among the cups.
In a bowl, beat together milk, 1/4 cup of the thawed concentrate, eggs and sugar.
Pour milk mixture evenly over bread cubes. Lightly press cubes into milk mixture.
Arrange custard cups in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place pan in oven.
Carefully pour very hot tap water into pan around custard cups to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove the cups from the baking pan.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on ham slices.
Roll up and cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: After crushing graham crackers into crumbs, add miniature marshmallows, chopped dates and pecans with the whipped Milnot (cream) which moistens ingredients.
Then divide into 3 rolls wrapped in wax paper then foil.
Keep frozen and remove shortly before serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute the onion in the butter.
Add ground beef and cook until well done.
Add 1 3/4 cups canned tomatoes and some water.
Add the beans, salt, bay leaf, sugar and chili powder.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Serve with tortillas or crackers.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: In a small bowl, cream together the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in the corn syrup and oats.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan.
Place frozen dinner rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix dry pudding, sugar and cinnamon together and pour over rolls.
Pour melted butter on top.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Whip egg whites stiff; fold in rest of ingredients.
Press down in greased pie plate.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: champagne salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
In a different bowl, combine pineapple, strawberries, nuts, bananas and Cool Whip. Add this mixture to the cream cheese mixture and stir.
Freeze entire mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan for about 8 hours. Set out about 20 minutes before serving. Serve while still partially frozen.

title: tex-mex chili chicken
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove.
Add remaining oil, onion, pepper and garlic. Saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt, cumin, oregano and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken
is cooked.
Serve in tortillas with cheese and sour cream.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain canned goods.
Blend sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and add crushed ice.

title: hot cherry peppers in oil
directions: Drain jar of peppers; cut peppers and remove seeds.
Place pepper halves in jar; peel garlic and add to peppers.
Cover with oil and sprinkle with oregano to taste.

title: bean cacciatora
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions in a frying pan. Drain off fat. Add rest of ingredients. Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: glazed broiled tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch slices. Place in single layer on baking sheet.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, 1 teaspoon parsley, chives, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese in a small bowl.
Spread mixture over each tomato slice. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes. Immediately transfer to broiler (6-inches from heat).
Broil until topping is golden, glazed and bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Serve at once.

title: soupreme skillet chicken
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise; slice diagonally in 1/2-inch pieces.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat. Add soup and seasonings.
Cover over low heat 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add zucchini and tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes more or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herbed onion biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well until stiff dough forms. Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 5 dozen.
(Can be made larger; use tablespoonful and bake a little longer.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cool and debone.
Cook vegetables in 2 cups chicken broth.
Add mushrooms, soup and chili powder.
Mix well. Add chicken and 3 cups cooked rice.
Mix well and put into large casserole.
Top with cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lo-cal cranberry salad
directions: Mix and set aside gelatin and water.
Chop in blender the cranberries (I use canned cranberries) and apple.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Add pineapple, banana and orange juice.
Chill in favorite dish or gelatin mold and serve.

title: chocolate frostie(tastes just like wendy's)
directions: Mix well. Pour into electric ice cream churn and freeze as directed.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix other ingredients with yeast.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Cook at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; let rise.
Divide in half and roll out.
Spoon over melted butter and cinnamon and sugar mixture on top.
Roll like a jellyroll.
Cut in small pieces and put in pan; let rise.
Put more cinnamon and sugar on top and spoon on melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in roaster.
Bake for 4 hours (more or less, depending on apple pulp thickness) at 300° to 325°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Put clean jars and lids into boiling water to sterilize.
Fill hot jars with apple butter.
Wipe off tops with clean cloth.
Put on hot lids and turn rings tight.
(Use hot pads.)
Let set undisturbed to cool.
Makes about 1/2 pint for each cup of apples.

title: symphony bar cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
As soon as you take out of oven, punch holes all through cake and pour sweetened milk over. Pour caramel over milk and frost with cream cheese frosting.
Then apply Cool Whip.
Chop candy and pour over Cool Whip.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until onions are tender.
Cook chicken by boiling 20 to 30 minutes.
Once thoroughly done, chop chicken into chunks.
Mix cooked chicken, onions, soups, milk and sour cream together.
Place mixture in an 11 x 13 pan (baking dish) and place in the oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Take the mixture out of the oven and cover with shredded cheese.
Place biscuits on top of the mixture.
Return dish to the oven and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and the biscuits are browned.

title: dilly beans
directions: Add dill, clove garlic and pepper in 2-quart jar.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over beans to fill jar.
Cover and seal.
Let sit 4 to 6 weeks.
The longer the better.
Serve chilled like pickles.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: *Mushrooms, zucchini, broccoli or whatever you have on hand. If using fresh broccoli, steam or microwave first.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell eggs; cut each half and remove yolks.
Mash.
Add all other ingredients to mashed yolks and mix until smooth.
Fill the whites with the mixture.

title: simple chicken italiano
directions: In skillet combine chicken and half the Italian dressing. Saute chicken until it starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Toss pasta with garlic and butter.
Serve vegetable and chicken over pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour apple cider into a coffee percolator.
Put candy and orange slices in percolator basket.
Candy will melt as cider perks.

title: perfect pie crust(recipe makes 5 pie crusts)
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and stir well with table fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until ingredients are crumbly.

title: green beans
directions: Put green beans in a pan with oil for 7 to 10 minutes, then add onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook until egg is done.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix well first 3 ingredients; pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch bits over top, then sprinkle nut topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail and pectin in a large saucepan; stir over high heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Stir in sugar and bring to a full boil.
Boil hard for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Pour into jelly jars.
Seal with 1/8 inch layer of hot paraffin.

title: greg's famous fruit breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bottom of 10-inch skillet with fresh fruit.
Add butter and brown sugar; sprinkle pecans over fruit.
Warm it up.
In a bowl, mix 7 eggs, sugar, vanilla and Bisquick.
Pour mix on top of fruit; cover and cook on low for 20 minutes.
Flip onto a plate; sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with syrup.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Add milk and eggs. Melt margarine and add to mixture; mix well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in 2 cups water with 1 teaspoon salt.
When cooked, remove and drain well.
Melt margarine.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; add milk and green pepper.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat
and add cheese spread.
Stir until well mixed.
Mix corn bread crumbs in 3 tablespoons melted margarine.

title: britt's lammin' good chili(pressure cooker chili)
directions: Heat pressure
cooker
and brown meat, onions and green pepper.
Add
remaining
ingredients,
except
kidney
beans. Close cover
securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe. Cook 5 minutes.
Turn
off burner and let pressure drop of its own accord.
Remove
lid, add beans and heat through.

title: churros
directions: Take a piece of dough in your hands and roll it into a long rope.
Fry in 2 inches oil, heated to 350° until golden.
Roll in sugar and serve hot!

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir very well.
Makes about 80 cups.

title: burgundy meat balls(serves 6)
directions: Cut each chicken breast into halves along the breastbone line. Remove the filet mignon, the finger size muscle on the back of each half.
Reserve for another use.
Flatten each breast half or supreme by pressing it gently with the palm of your hand.

title: english toffee
directions: Chop almonds and spread 1/2 cup in bottom of buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.
Combine butter and sugar in heavy skillet; cook, stirring until boiling point is reached.
Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly to soft-crack stage, 270° to 280°.
Pour carefully over almonds.
Let stand for about 10 minutes, until top is set.
Sprinkle chocolate over top of candy. When heat of candy has melted chocolate, smooth with spatula.
Sprinkle remaining almonds over chocolate.
Let stand until cold.
Break into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain, then add onion, mustard, beans, brown sugar, ketchup, molasses and Worcestershire sauce. Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: green tomato sweet pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes thin.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let remain 24 hours.
Rinse in cold water, then soak in alum water 2 to 3 hours (use alum the size of a partridge egg).
Rinse again.
Now weigh them and put in kettle of cold ginger water.
Let come to a boil. Add vinegar, sugar, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Boil only a few minutes.
Boil down syrup.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and chill until ready to serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Microwave:
In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine soup and milk.
Stir in noodles, peas, pimento and tuna.
Cover and microwave on High 9 minutes or until hot, stirring twice during heating.
Meanwhile, in small saucepan in hot butter, stir bread crumbs until lightly browned.
Sprinkle over noodle mixture. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
This will make three loaf pans of bread and makes nice gifts.
Also freezes for short period.
Bake one for yourself and share the other two.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Mix oil and rest of ingredients together.
Scrub potatoes and cut into wedges.
Coat potatoes and place in pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
A small amount of oil may be put in pan before the potatoes to keep them from sticking.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a frying pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until brown (about 20 minutes).
Add bouillon and mushrooms.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove cover. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cashew chicken and rice
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute chicken in oil for 2 minutes or until tender.
Add bamboo shoots, celery and water chestnuts.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in cashews and pimentos. Blend cornstarch, seasoned pepper and soy sauce.
Stir in broth. Pour into chicken mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave poached salmon
directions: Combine all
ingredients
except
fish and garnishes in 2-quart microproof	casserole.
Cover
and	place in microwave oven.
Cook on
High 7 minutes.
Put in fish.
Cook 5 minutes. Turn fish over
carefully
and
cook 3 to 5 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing lid.
Serve with lots of lemon or lime, hot or chilled.
Garnish with parsley.

title: oven fried honey chicken
directions: In large bowl, whisk the honey and vinegar. Pour bread crumbs into separate bowl and set aside. Spread oil over foil-lined baking dish large enough to hold all chicken in single layer. Roll chicken in honey mixture, then bread crumbs and place in pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cooked thoroughly.

title: watermelon salad with watercress
directions: Cut watermelon in half horizontally. Reserve half for another use. With remaining half, use a small paring knife to carefully cut around the fruit, just inside the rind. Cut fruit in the melon crosswise into 1-inch slices (leaving the rind intact). Cut underneath each slice and remove from the shell. Pile slices back into the shell. Cover and chill up to 6 hours.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cheesy dip
directions: *This type of cheese usually comes in a roll or jar.

title: ralph's egg rolls
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, cook sausage until it loses its color.
Combine vegetables with sausage; sprinkle soy sauce over top of mixture and cook for one or two minutes.
Mix well. Remove from heat; drain in colander and let cool.
Put two tablespoons of mixture in the middle of the wrapper; fold and seal with a little water.

If you are not frying immediately, put a damp paper towel over the egg rolls to keep them from drying out. Heat oil in pot or deep skillet, drop egg rolls in and deep fry. Serve with sweet-sour sauce, hot mustard, etc.
Yield:

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake according to directions on box. Pour 1/2 of cake mix into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Prepare 12 ounces Kraft caramels, 1 can Eagle Brand condensed milk and 1/2 cup butter into saucepan and melt over slow heat.
Pour over cooled cake.
Sprinkle 6 ounces chocolate chips and 1 cup chopped pecans over caramel mixture on cake.
Then pour remaining batter and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook until beans are tender.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate the zucchini into a bowl and drain.
Stir in the eggs, flour, Parmesan cheese, chives, parsley, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
If mixture looks too liquidy, add 1 more tablespoon flour.
Drop the batter onto oiled skillet (like pancakes). Brown.

title: sweet-sour beans
directions: Drain beans; place in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, covered, over moderate heat, 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not cook dry.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream or mix well, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
These are a soft cookie.

title: potato filling balls
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls or use ice cream scoop.
Place side by side in buttered baking dish.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool.
Add Seven-Up, strawberries, celery, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm. Yields 6 servings.

title: sunburst yellow cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into bowl before mixing.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, 3 minutes on high speed.
Ice with your favorite icing.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted). Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup Cool Whip; pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Drizzle with chocolate topping just before serving, if desired.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain and dispose of the liquid in the jar of dill pickles. (If the pickles are whole cucumbers, slice or strip.
The sliced dill is better.)
Put the cucumbers back into the jar, a layer at a time, a layer of pickles and a layer of sugar.
Turn jar upside down and let set a few days.
Shake.
If not sweet enough, add more sugar and let set again.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Marinate steak for several hours in the mixture of remaining ingredients.
Broil for 4 minutes on a side for rare or to desired doneness.
Slice thinly diagonally and arrange on a platter. Makes 6 servings.

title: german carrots
directions: Saute for 5 minutes.
Add beer, salt, pepper, sugar and sprinkle with dill weed.
Cover and cook until beer is absorbed and carrots tender.
Then saute for a few more minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown together hamburg, butter, onion, garlic and celery. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry corn cake
directions: In saucepan, combine heat and sugar.
Bring just to a boil. Sprinkle corn meal gradually into mixture, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Fold in strawberries and turn into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown and firm.
Remove and cool.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: big red cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake box. Cool cake and set aside. In a medium bowl, mix jello with one cup cold water and instead of one cup boiling water use the Big Red Soda.

Mix until completely dissolved. After cake cools use a fork to polk holes in the cake, cover the whole cake with the punctures. Pour Jello mixture over the cake and allow the cake to soak up all the mixture. Frost the cake with whip cream and refrigerate for an hour. Now its ready to eat.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and chopped figs and add to mixture. Beat eggs until frothy and add milk. Sift part of flour with baking powder. Add remaining flour. Add alternately to creamed mixture with egg mixture, beat well.Add chopped raisins and almonds, mix well. Pour into pan and bake at 375° for 30 min.

title: raspberry smacks
directions: Bottom Layer:
Crumble first 7 ingredients together until mixed.
Press into ungreased pan.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot, over medium-high heat.
Add peppers, onions and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove to a bowl. Stir-fry pork until cooked through.
Mix pineapple juice (minus 1/4 cup) and last 5 ingredients.
Stir into skillet.
Add veggies and pineapple; bring to a boil cooking 1 minute until thick. Serve over rice (4 to 6 servings).

title: g.g.'s porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Form into balls about the size of a lime. Dilute tomato soup with stewed tomatoes (chop the tomatoes).
Put meatballs and tomato sauce into pan. Cover and simmer gently for 1 hour.

title: carrot banana bread(1 loaf)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar. Add eggs; mix well. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Gradually add to the creamed mixture alternately with bananas. Stir in carrots and pecans. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool.

title: party dogs
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Brown beef and onion, drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread mixture in bottom of pie pan.
In mixing bowl, beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth or 1 minute with hand held mixer.
Pour over beef in pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and lemon peel. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and lightly browned on top.

title: chili dip
directions: Mash tamales. Mix with chilli, salsa and cheese. Spread in 8 x 8 inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and olives. Bake covered 20 minutes at 350 degree or until heated through. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces in bottom of punch bowl or other large bowl.
Mix jello according to directions; partially set.
Pour over angel food cake.
Layer the fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Make instant pudding according to directions; spread over fruit.
Spread Cool Whip on top; garnish with strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: warm chocolate icing
directions: May use more or less cocoa for desired taste.

title: pork and potato scallop
directions: Brown steaks on both sides in lard drippings. Place half the sliced potatoes in a 2 1/2-quart casserole and top with 3 pork cube steaks.
Place remaining potatoes on cube steaks and top with remaining steaks.
Stir milk into soup. Add onion, pimiento, salt and pepper and pour over steak and potatoes.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender. Serves 6.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skins until tender.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in greased shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; cook until thick.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes.
I use frozen orange juice and dilute as directed.
This can be made the night before, if desired, then baked.

title: healthy blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, milk and eggs and mix well.
Fold in bananas and blueberries.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: gourmet shrimp
directions: Mix flour, fresh dill, paprika and salt together.
Drain and dry shrimp thoroughly.
Coat evenly with flour mixture.
Melt margarine in preheated skillet.
Add shrimp.
Turn frequently until they are coated with margarine and appear glossy.
Add mushrooms, shallots and milk.
Warm thoroughly.
Sprinkle cheese on top; cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over white rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Stir in eggs, added 1 at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add milk and soda, flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Grease Bundt pan.
Pour in mixture and cook 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Loosen cake and invert pan.

title: christmas eggs
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Great for brunches!
Serves 10 people.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer. Bake in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, if desired, and cool completely.
May be served with or without frosting.
If frosting is desired, use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomatoes in bowl.
Whisk together the oil, vinegar, sugar and basil.
Stir in onions.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over tomatoes.
Marinate for a couple of hours.

title: sweet and spicy chicken
directions: Coat chicken in taco seasoning and brown in oil, drain. Combine salsa and preserves stir into skillet.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes or till chicken is no longer pink.
Simmer till desired thickness.
Serve over rice.

title: butter dips(quick bread)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in pan in oven and remove. (You may find you need additional butter.)
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add milk; stir.
Knead lightly.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick into an 8-inch square.
With floured knife, cut into strips 4 inches wide, then cut crosswise to make 18 sticks.
Dip sticks in butter; place in 2 rows in pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 18 Butter Dips.
Delicious!

title: pecan raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in unbaked 9-inch pie crust shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lila's apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and egg together.
Blend flour, soda, nutmeg, vanilla and salt; then add apples and nuts.
Mix all together and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pea supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy crab & artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In medium mixing bowl, blend together cream cheese and mayo until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and place in glass pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, 15-18 minutes, until heated through and slightly browned.
Serve with crackers or French bread.
Serves 8.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla. Cool.
When thick, ice cake.

title: chicken sate
directions: About 2 1/2 Hours Before Serving:
With meat mallet or dull edge of French knife, pound each chicken breast half to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut chicken breasts lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips.

title: grilled cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half, then slice each half into 5 pieces. Place cabbage in center of large piece of foil.
Place 2 tablespoons of both the butter and lemon pepper on the cabbage. Repeat 4 times.
Wrap so cabbage can steam.
Place on grill with whatever else you're cooking.
Takes 20 minutes or so.

title: meltaways
directions: In medium bowl, with pastry fork, blend cottage cheese with 1 cup butter. Sift in flour, then blend until dough forms a ball (can use your hands for this).
Start heating oven to 400°.
Grease 3 cookie sheets. Divide dough in thirds.
On lightly floured, cloth covered board, roll out 1/3 of dough 1/8 inch thick and circular in shape. Brush with some of melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar, a little cinnamon and 1/4 cup of chopped walnuts.
Cut circle into 16 pie shaped wedges.
Beginning at outer edge, roll up each piece tightly, then place point side down on cookie sheet. Repeat with rest of pieces. Beat egg yolk with water then use to brush tops of cookies.
Bake about 20 minutes or until golden. Repeat with other 2/3 of dough.

title: memaws chilli
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Add all ingredients, simmer 2 hours.
Serve with cornbread and cabbage.

title: vlasic whole dills
directions: Will need 42 or 46 ounce jar.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Thin the cream cheese with milk.
Add all other ingredients except pecans and butter and place in an 8-inch Pyrex pie plate. Brown pecans in butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove stems from mushrooms and set aside.
Place mushroom caps in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Chop mushroom stems to make 1/2 cup.
Save remaining stems for another use.
Chop ham.
Place chopped mushrooms and ham in bowl.
Press garlic with garlic press and place in bowl with remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Use a small spoon to place mixture into mushroom caps.
Pat down.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Yield:

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix altogether in 5-quart ice cream bucket.
Freeze, stirring a little.
Serve with 7-Up or sour.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Beat egg, flour, sugar and 1 tablespoon salt well with fork or beater.
Peel tomatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Broil bacon until crisp; mince fine.

title: cherry pizza cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 cup of oats to 6 tablespoons margarine on low speed until crumbly.
Set 1/2 cup mixture aside.
To remaining crumbs blend in egg.
Press into pizza pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
In a bowl, add remaining oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts, cinnamon, brown sugar and crumb mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Spread filling on baked crust and sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
May decorate with cream cheese icing.

title: microwaved stuffed peppers
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion and seasonings.
Fill peppers; place in a 10-inch microwave pie plate.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 20 to 22 minutes or until peppers are tender and meat is no longer red.
Remove plastic; top with cheese slices.
Re-cover and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Cream well.
Add vanilla.
Divide batter in half.
Add the following to one-half:
1 teaspoon of cinnamon, 1 teaspoon allspice, 1/2 cloves and 1/4 pound raisins.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Stir in the flour, liquid from one can of green beans, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Add the drained green beans and crumbled bacon. Heat until warmed through.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: *Amount of cheese depends on whether you want to make it into a ball or use it as a spread; more cheese for ball, less if for spreading.

title: bulghur wheat casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet and brown the onion.
Add the bouillon and tomato sauce.
Season.
Add the wheat.
Cover and simmer lightly until all liquid is absorbed (20 to 30 minutes).
Add cooked broccoli.
Cover top of casserole with grated cheese.
Melt under broiler until lightly browned.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, whipping cream and pecans. Bring to boil and cook until forms soft but firm ball, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon. Takes approximately 1 hour. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Add vanilla and salt and beat until very firm until it starts clinging together in a ball. Takes about 20 minutes of beating. Pour into greased 9 x 13 cake pan. Very Rich!

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Place milk, candy bars and marshmallows in top of double boiler and melt.
When melted, set out of water and cool completely.
Fold frozen topping into the chocolate mixture. Pour into pie crust and chill for 3 hours or until ready to serve.

title: california salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: delicious chex muddy buddies mix
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl and set aside.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large Glad-Lock plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: winter fruit compote* * * * *
directions: Hildy and family lived a block from us on Oakland Plantation in South Carolina.
She was originally from Winnepeg, Manitoba, Canada.
Our husbands had been in the same AF Wing when we were in Germany and they were in France.
Many years and many moves later, they are looking for a house in our little part of Texas.

title: broiled salmon
directions: Note: Best to use a hot plate and an older nonstick pan and plug the hot plate in outdoors and do your cooking out there. Makes 6 servings.

title: date nut roll
directions: Crush crackers in food processor; mix with Eagle Brand milk. Cut nuts, dates and fruit together.
Pour lemon juice and water over them; stir well.
Roll cracker crumbs that have been mixed with the milk in the sugar (just enough to keep from sticking). Spread out same as biscuit dough.
Spread nuts, dates and fruit on dough; roll it like a jelly roll.
Let chill about 6 to 8 hours. Slice as you would a jelly roll.

title: egg casserole
directions: Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk; add cheese. Season with 1/4 teaspoon each of thyme, marjoram and basil.
Make 3 layers of egg, bacon and sauce.
Sprinkle snipped parsley over top.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° or until bubbly.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix and pat out in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes one 9-inch pie crust for cream pies.

title: easy baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Rub turkey outside with cooking oil. Salt and pepper on inside.
Place whole onion and celery in cavity. For turkey up to 12 pounds, use 1 pint water in roaster with rack. Over 12 pounds, use 1 quart water.
Cover roaster.
Place in oven. Bake 1 hour.
DO NOT OPEN OVEN DOOR UNTIL NEXT MORNING!!
This turkey will be ready.

title: beetle hats
directions: Place bologna in a pan.
Put 2 tablespoons of creamed potatoes in the center of bologna.
Put cheese on top of potatoes.
Place in oven at 375° and cook until cheese is melted and bologna starts to roll up and brown around the edges.
Good for kids!!

title: zuppa di pesce(fish soup)
directions: In a large pot, saute leeks and garlic in oil. Add paste when browned.
Add water and crushed tomatoes. Boil.
Add seafood and spices.
Cook until fish is cooked through.
Serve alone as a soup or over pasta.
Less than 200 calories per serving.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Place batter into 2 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: quick onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan or Dutch oven over low heat (225°).
Add onions and cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add beef broth, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
While soup is heating, arrange bread slices on cookie sheet.
Spread the 1 1/2 tablespoons butter over slices and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in a preheated broiler about 4-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve soup in bowls topped with a slice of bread.
Makes about 2 quarts or 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into thirds; roll into small balls.
Grease Bundt pan.
Drop balls into pan; cover bottom well.
In small pot, melt butter, sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour over balls. Continue to layer balls and sauce mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and pineapple.
Combine both mixtures together.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: cake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and then add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken in a skillet with oil until done.
Add soy sauce, onion and green pepper.
When done, add salad dressing, cover and simmer on low.
Serve with rice; top with sour cream.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Bring cocoa, milk and sugar to full rolling boil.
Boil to soft ball stage (test in cold water).
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and salt.
Beat with beater until it has lost its shine.
Pour in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix together and heat on low first 5 ingredients until most of the chocolate is dissolved.

Pour into a bowl and mix in vanilla. Chill until the mixture begins to take the form of the bowl. While the mixture is chilling, whip heavy cream in a separate bowl until it takes the consistency of whipped cream.
Slowly fold in small amounts of the whipped cream to the chilled chocolate mixture until all is mixed together.
Chill and serve.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream milk and lemon juice with mixer.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Use two graham cracker pie crusts. Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Mix in a big saucepan, chopped chicken, broth and soup.
Let it come to a boil.
Turn heat down and add noodles.
Stir so noodles do not stick together.
Continue to cook until noodles are tender.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco in a pan.
Add sugar and beat thoroughly.
When fluffy, add flour slowly.
Then add nuts and vanilla extract.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sandy's cheese balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form 2 balls.
Roll each in additional chopped nuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple pudding
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix together with butter, sugars and apples.
Mix in nuts and raisins. Put in a large baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until it pulls away from sides of pan.

title: spinach 7 layer salad
directions: Put half of spinach in shallow bowl.
Add eggs and the rest of the spinach.
Top with onion rings and peas.
Mix mayo, yogurt and sour cream.
Spread over top and sprinkle with cheeses and bacon. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mash up strawberries and add sugar.
Put over cake and top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine jello and tomato juice; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make in mold and put on lettuce leaves.

title: mama's southern dressing
directions: Cook large pan of cornbread, cook and crumble.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Fill 18 greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to wire racks.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Cookies are softer if they are a little undercooked.

title: old fashioned floating island
directions: Heat milk almost to boiling point. Mix sugar, flour and beaten eggs together.
Add heated milk and return to low fire and cook, stirring constantly.
Custard is done when it coats the spoon. Add vanilla and pour into large bowl.

title: orange-blossom muffins
directions: Combine egg, sugar, orange juice and salad oil; add biscuit mix and beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Stir in marmalade and pecans. Grease muffin pans or line with paper baking cups; fill 2/3 full. Sprinkle with Spicy Topping.
Bake muffins in oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 14 muffins.

title: crescent dinner roll dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.

Roll out each dinner roll, add a little chicken in the center, roll up and put in baking pan. Mix both soups and chicken broth together and pour over dumplings. Bake for 45 minutes or until brown on top, at 325 degrees.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift the flour and sugar into a large mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, heat the butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola until boiling.
Pour this over the flour and sugar mixture, then mix thoroughly.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows and mix well. Then batter will be thin and the marshmallows will come to the top. Bake at 350° in a sheet pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place in an ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over biscuits; coat thoroughly.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook pie filling ingredients until thick.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and oranges.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix everything and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut cookies and bake on sheet for 8 minutes at 350°.
They're fattening.

title: mamaw borders' broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli until about 1/2 done.
Add celery, hard-boiled eggs, olives, onion and water chestnuts.
Add Miracle Whip and lemon juice to taste.

title: pizza chicken
directions: In 2-quart microwave dish place chicken and spaghetti sauce. Microwave covered on High for 13 minutes.
Turn chicken over and microwave covered for 15 minutes more.
Sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Spread Mozzarella over top and microwave 1 to 2 minutes more until Mozzarella is melted.
Serve with side of spaghetti.

title: nutty o's
directions: In large pan, heat brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in cereal and nuts; mix well.
Spread on greased baking pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Bake for 15 minutes; cool for 10 minutes.
Stir to loosen from pan.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 16 cups.

title: tofu burgers
directions: Drain and mash tofu.
Combine ingredients and mix well. Form into burgers and bake at 350° on sprayed cookie sheet for 30 to 45 minutes, turning when golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: brandied cranberries
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar.
Place in covered casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Add brandy after the cranberries are baked.

title: margaret's sausage pies
directions: Fry peppers, onions and sausage together on medium heat.
Add the remaining ingredients, turn stove to low and stir until thickened.
Use your own pastry or Hungry Jack biscuits.
One biscuit will make enough for four.
Then fill small pastry shells. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crust is brown.
Use small muffin tins for pastry shells.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Soak Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to jello that has been dissolved in 1 cup of hot water before you add the cup of cold water.
Put cranberries and orange that has been peeled and cut up, through food chopper.
Add sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Add celery and nuts.
Stir in jello mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: dream cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add oil, vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients until blended well.
Fold in by hand the Rice Krispies, coconut, oats and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Peel and grate zucchini squash; then set aside.

title: cookie surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and food color. Work flour and salt into mixture (if dough is dry mix in 1 tablespoon milk).
Mold dough around cherry or Kiss.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until set but not brown.
Cool.
Dip into icing and decorate with sprinkles or coconut.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop cherries, nuts and pineapple.
Roll in 1 cup flour.
Save enough fruit and nuts to decorate top.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder 3 times, adding beaten eggs. Mix well.
Add nuts, fruit and flavoring and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, then 30 minutes at 300°.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order; mash bananas and add last.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in middle of loaf.
Use 1 large loaf pan or 2 small pans.

title: italian salad
directions: Wash lettuce and cut or tear into bite-size pieces; add rest of the ingredients and toss.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix carrots, onion and green peppers in large bowl.
Mix soup and remaining ingredients and heat through.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks.

title: baked spinach dip loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Cut a 1 1/2 inch slice off top of bread and set aside.
Carefully hollow out bottom leaving a 1/2 inch shell.
Cube removed bread and set aside.
Fill the shell with spinach dip; replace top.
Wrap in heavy duty foil and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until dip is heated through.
Open foil carefully.
Serve warm with bread cubes and vegetables.

title: chocolate chip banana bread(makes one 16 slice loaf)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of one 9 x 5-inch or two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, combine sugar and margarine; beat until light and fluffy.
Add bananas, sour cream and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend well. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.
Best when served the next day; also freezes well.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil your chicken until it is done. Take one cup of the broth and put in the freezer to cool. Debone the chicken and put the meat back in the broth. After the refrigerated broth has completely cooled pour it in a medium sized bowl. Add flour until you can handle the mixture.

Put a thin layer of flour on a cutting sheet. Put 1/4 of the mixture and work some of the flour in if you need to. Flour a rolling pin and roll out the mixture. Put chicken and broth on high heat. Add pepper and salt. When this has come to a rolling boil cut dumplings in pieces and drop in broth. Continue doing this until all dumplings are gone. Lower heat to medium low and add milk. Stir your dumplings slightly and let cook for about 7 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: chocolate cool whip pie
directions: Grate off a little of the chocolate bar and save for decorations.
Melt chocolate bar.
Mix with Cool Whip with electric mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Decorate with chocolate shavings.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours.

title: beef and rice
directions: Brown chuck in skillet; set aside.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Add egg and scramble.
Add meat and rice.
Stir well, then add remaining ingredients, including bean juice.
Stir gently until hot through.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Shape into balls and place in 8 x 8 pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
No salt!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute butter, green pepper and onion.
Combine corn, eggs, muffin mix, sour cream and cheese.
Add sauteed ingredients to corn mixture.
Bake in a casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let chill several hours before serving.

title: tuna broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Mix tuna, broccoli, 5 ounces cheese and half can of onions.
In separate bowl mix soup and milk.
Pour 3/4 of soup/milk into tuna mixture.
Spoon into flour tortillas and roll. Place tortillas in greased 9x13 inch baking dish.
Pour remaining soup/milk on top of tortillas.
Bake covered 40 minutes.
Put remaining cheese and onions on top and bake uncovered 5-10 minutes or until cheese melts. 4 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter.
Add flour and salt.
Form dough in ball.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Mix preserves, nuts, peel and cornstarch.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll each ball to 1/8-inch thick (10 x 12-inch rectangle).
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves mix in center of each square.
Fold corners into middle and seal by pinching.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes. When cooled, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: cherry nut dessert
directions: Spread cherries over bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries and then drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: banana or strawberry punch
directions: Heat sugar and 3 cups water until dissolved.
Add remaining water and all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Pour into container and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before serving.
Add ginger ale and serve.
May add red or yellow food coloring.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Slightly brown ground beef, then simmer 45 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the cabbage after cooking the other ingredients for about 15 minutes.
Add the cabbage.
After all the ingredients are added, simmer for an additional hour.
Add instant rice about 4 minutes at the end of the cooking.
Cook until rice is tender.
Serve hot.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Microwave chocolate on medium for 5 to 6 minutes or until melted.
Stir in peppermint candy and food coloring.
Spread chocolate mixture on a 15 x 12-inch baking sheet that has been covered with foil (shiny side up).
Place in freezer 5 to 10 minutes until firm.
Peel foil from candy and break into pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Layer ham, potatoes and onions.
Season potato layer and add dots of butter.
Mix flour and milk and pour over layers.
Layer in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook over coals for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May also use a tripod.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Karo syrup.
Coat pecans with flour; add to mixture and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use any or all of these ingredients to suit your taste and cupboard.
Drain any canned fruits.
Mix fruits and chill well to blend flavors.
Serve as is or add one of the following dressings:

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar and cream until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat thoroughly. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add with milk. Add the 5 extracts. Pour in a 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine butter with 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Press onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour, sifted with salt and soda, alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef 'n tater bake
