directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper and pat into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain fat.
Combine mashed potatoes with 3/4 cup cheese and then spread over meat.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: grandma simon's bean soup
directions: In most of these soup recipes "stock or water" appears on the list of ingredients.
You can get delicious soups using plain water as the vehicle, but vegetable stock lends a fuller, more vegetable-y flavor.
Stock-making is an old-fashioned approach to soup; it enriches the atmosphere of our modern, expedient kitchens.
Further, it makes good use of vegetable scraps which would otherwise be thrown away.

title: upside-down cobbler
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Pour mixture on melted oleo. Top with fruit (reserve juice).
Pour juice on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in moderate oven or until golden brown.

title: alaska salad
directions: Combine whipped topping and orange gelatin in bowl; mix well. Add cottage cheese, mandarin oranges and pineapple; mix well. Pour into serving dish and chill for 4 hours.
I decorate the top with another can of drained mandarin oranges to give it some color.
May use other flavors of gelatin with your choice of fruits if desired.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: high energy shake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.

title: candied squash rings
directions: Cut squash crosswise into 1-inch thick slices; discard seeds. Arrange in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and water; cook and stir until bubbly.
Spoon over squash.
Continue baking uncovered for 15 minutes more.
Baste often.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: bobbi's mashed potato candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.
Chill.

title: snow white frosting(total cooking time:  4 to 5 minutes)
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt.
Insert temperature probe and cook on 70 (Roast) set at 200°.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add hot syrup to egg whites, beating continuously.
Continue beating 5 minutes or until frosting is thick and fluffy.
While beating, add vanilla.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, olives and salsa.
Set aside.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour 1/3 of soup mixture into chicken mixture.
Stir. Place chicken mixture down center of tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold and place seam side down in baking dish.
Makes 12. Pour soup mixture over top and sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: Butter Bundt or tube pan.
Cut rolls in 2 to 3 pieces.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls, then sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Melt butter and brown sugar in small pan.
Pour this mixture over rolls.
Cover pan with foil, then towel and leave on the counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes (with foil), then uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix jello, Kool-Aid and sugar with hot water, then add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Usually have to at least double recipe.

title: mom's chicken rice soup
directions: Cook,
debone
and
cut up chicken, saving broth.
Cook rice in
water with bouillon cube.
Add enough water to broth to
make 3
cups, then add 1/2 teaspoon celery seed, 1/2 teaspoon
parsley flakes and 2 bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil. When
bouillon is dissolved, add the chicken and rice.
Simmer until ready to serve. Corn may also be added.
This makes the kind of thick soup my Dad likes.

title: mathews county virginia crab cakes
directions: Steam the crabs. Cool and pick. Add crab, bread, seafood seasoning, salad dressing, salt, pepper, egg and Worcestershire sauce to a large bowl.
Mix together.
The contents should not be soupy, but you should be able to make into cakes.
Heat skillet with oil. Fry until golden brown on each side.
Mix horseradish and ketchup for sauce.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Put potatoes into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Pour evaporated milk over potatoes.
Season pork chops with onion, salt and pepper.
Trim fat.
Cook fat until crisp, then remove from skillet.
Brown chops slowly on both sides, then put on top of potatoes in baking dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili powder
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Cover bottom of pan with pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with pecans if desired.

title: cauliflower marinara
directions: Steam cauliflower until nearly tender.
Place on platter. Spoon on tomato sauce, sprinkle with cheese. Cover with foil and let stand 2 or 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries.
Sift together salt, flour, cinnamon and soda in bowl.
Add berry mix to dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (2 large or 3 small).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: kyle's dinosaur toast
directions: With dinosaur cookie cutter, cut shapes from bread.
Dip each shape into orange juice and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 250° oven for 20 minutes or until toasted.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla together.
Add flour and roll into balls, make dent in each ball with thimble or finger.
Put a small amount of jelly in dent.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and eggs in a large mixing bowl, set aside.
Combine cocoa and butter over a low heat.
Add this mixture to the other, blend well and add vanilla and pecans.
Pour this into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Brownies should be fudgy.
Don't overbake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 24.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and pepper; drain.
Cover noodles with water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Put all together and season with salt.
Add cheese slices.
Bake in oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Pour milk into a small glass or metal bowl; place beaters for electric mixer into the bowl.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.
Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Line bottom and sides of pie plate with wafers.
Beat milk until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and drink mix; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Spoon over wafers; freeze for at least 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all of above ingredients except butter and corn flakes. Melt butter, pour over mixture and sprinkle corn flakes over top. Bake in large casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Add onion, celery and dash of seasoned salt.
Break dried beef into small pieces and mix with rest of mixture.
Great dip on crackers!

title: fast cookies(blitzgeback)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and flour.
Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread the batter evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over batter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and sliced almonds.
Bake in a hot 375° oven thirty minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Measure flour after sifting.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend flour and shortening.
Add milk; blend.
Drop onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: eye of round roast
directions: You will need 1 oven bag, regular size.

title: cheese and egg sandwich spread
directions: Cook together the first 6 ingredients until thickened.
Cool and add the remaining ingredients. Makes a very good sandwich on wheat bread.

title: crunch chocolate pie
directions: Coat 8-inch pie plate with nonstick spray.
In large nonstick saucepan, warm peanut butter and honey over low heat until peanut butter has melted.
Remove pan from heat and stir in cereal. Press cereal mixture into bottom and up sides of pie plate. Freeze 1 hour.

title: indian chicken
directions: Melt butter; add chicken and brown.
Remove chicken.
Add garlic and onion; cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken, salt, ginger, chili, tomatoes and yogurt.
Mix lightly, cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Add cashews and coconuts.
Cook 5 minutes. To cornstarch, add cream slowly.
Stir until dissolved, then stir into pot, stirring constantly, until boiling; simmer 5 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach into small pieces.
Add drained and washed bean sprouts.
Add diced eggs and crumbed bacon.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and egg yolk in small casserole dish. Add juices. Cook on High power in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir once. Cool and fold into whipped cream.

title: chili stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a thin slice from stem of peppers and remove all seed and membranes.
Wash inside and outside of peppers and set aside.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
Stuff the peppers and stand peppers upright in an ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Mix sugar and vinegar; add seed.
Pour over the mixture.
Bring to a boiling point. Reduce heat; simmer for 25 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pickled pig feet
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil; set aside. Scald, scrape and clean the pigs feet.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and let stand for 4 to 8 hours.
Wash the feet in clean water; place in hot water and cook until tender, but not long enough for meat to come off the bones.
Pack in jars; cover the boiling vinegar solution.
Process the sealed jars in water for 90 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put water, chicken cubes and broccoli together; boil.
Put margarine on low heat and melt, stirring in flour slowly, on low. Heat continuously, stirring, making a paste.
Add water mixture a little at a time until completely mixed.
Add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer, then add half and half.
Simmer about 1/2 hour, until done.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out ball of dough.
Knead for 1 minute, then pat into a round, rather flat cake, about the size of a 9-inch pie pan.
Put dough on buttered cookie sheet and cut a large cross in the top.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 40 minutes.
Loaf is done when it sounds hollow when you tap it.

title: dill 'n chive potatoes
directions: Place scrubbed potatoes in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave, covered, on High 8 to 9 minutes or until just tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir to coat potatoes.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix sausage with bread crumbs and egg.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Fill mushrooms and place on cookie sheet.
Place square of cheese the size of mushroom on each.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Soften ice cream and spread over a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle crushed cookies over top.
Next spread Cool Whip over top. Freeze. Cut in squares. Kids might like this for a birthday party.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra, pepper and garlic in 5 pint jars.
Mix other ingredients with water.
Bring to a boil and pour over okra in jars 1/2 inch from top.
Seal jars with water bath.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, wheat germ and soda in large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, buttermilk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just to moisten.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bake at 400° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: marinade for venison
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place venison in enamel or earthenware bowl.
Pour marinade over it.
Cover with cheesecloth.
Let stand at least 24 hours or up to 4 days in a cool but not refrigerated temperature.
Turn meat often to thoroughly marinate.
Cook the meat in the marinade, or roast it and use marinade for gravy.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine jello and water, stirring until well dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, stirring until all chunks are broken up.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Stir in pineapple, mint and nuts.
Drop sour cream into jello by teaspoonfuls so that each serving will have a bit of sour cream in it.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: lo-fat chicken with vegies and pasta
directions: Saute zucchini, pepper and onion in a vegetable spray (i.e., Pam); set aside in bowl.
In same pan saute boneless chicken, cut up into small chunks or strips and when cooked put in vegetables and add chicken broth.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Pour over pasta and enjoy.

title: do ahead sausage souffle
directions: Lay bread in well greased 8-1/2 x 11 inch pan. Sprinkle cheese evenly over top. Arrange sausage pieces on top of cheese. Beat eggs with 2-1/4 cups milk and mustard. Add soup and the remaining milk. Mix well. Spoon over bread, cheese and sausage layers. Cover tightly. Refrigerate overnight. Put in cold oven, turn the oven to 300° and bake for 1-1/2 hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute bacon, onions and green pepper.
Cook bacon until 3/4 done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use whole grain rice, not bag rice.
Stir well; bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Add oleo. Let cool.
After cooling, add apples and pour into oblong dish. Cover with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add the eggs and beat until fluffy.
Mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well and add to the butter and sugar.
Add the apples.
It becomes quite thick.
Place in a buttered 9-inch pan and spread it well. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool on a rack.
You can also serve it warm, topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stay in refrigerator until well chilled.
This gets better the longer it sits.

title: guacamole
directions: Just before serving:
In covered blender container at low speed, blend all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, coating well.
Let stand, covered, overnight in refrigerator.

title: scripture cake
directions: If the correct ingredients are chosen from the references given, a delicious fruit cake will be assured.
The ingredients are found entirely in the Old Testament.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Mix yogurt, garlic, ginger, lime juice and spices.
Rub chickens inside and out with mixture.
Place in a bowl and pour rest of marinade over.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Turn chickens if not completely covered at least once.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove chickens from marinade. Place in pan and roast until done, about 1 hour.
Baste with marinade.
Disjoint and serve with wedge of lime and onion. Serves 8.
Half chicken contains 207 calories, quarter chicken contains 105 calories.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer ground beef, carrots, potatoes and onions.
Mix together tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Pour over top of vegetables.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together in medium bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Combine egg with pumpkin and milk.

Stir in raisins. Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to mix lightly. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over each muffin. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until done and nicely browned.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and butter in large bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until both are completely melted.
Stir in 2 cups of sugar. Mix in 4 eggs and vanilla.
Stir in 1 cup of flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread into greased foil lined 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: linda's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems from fresh mushroom caps.
Chop into fine pieces. Set aside.
Saute mushroom pieces and onion in butter until tender.
Mix crumbled bacon and bread crumbs.
Stuff this mixture into mushroom caps and bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pita bites
directions: Cut pita breads into quarters.
Spread the insides with butter or margarine.
Hold the pieces open as you sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Close each and place onto a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes. Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain. Combine soup, eggs,
mayonnaise
and
cheese. Mix well. Add broccoli. Pour
into buttered
casserole and bake in oven at 325° until set.
Remove from oven.	Cover with chips and bake until light brown. Serves 4.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil whole red potatoes.
Allow to cool.
Peel and chop into fairly large pieces.
Chop eggs, celery and onions and add to potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add approximately 1/2 jar Miracle Whip.

title: rhubarb crunch (1)
directions: Mix until crumbly: flour, rolled oats, cinnamon, brown sugar and melted butter. Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 inch baking pan.
Cover with 4 c. diced rhubarb or apples. Sprinkle on a dash of salt or baking soda over rhubarb before sauce is poured on to take away the tart taste.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs and water until eggs are well beaten. Add cake mix and melted margarine.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
This beating makes the layers light and soft.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix up ingredients except lemon icing.
Add just a little bit of water.
Put mixture into pan and bake at 250°.
Add icing after cooling.

title: hash browns supreme
directions: Put the hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together and spread over the top of the potatoes.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May use corn flake crumbs for topping.

title: oriental cherry chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt and pepper, dip into flour. Fry in hot fat.
When chicken is done, remove from pan.
Pour out drippings, measure 1/3 cup and return to pan.
Add cherries, (reserving a small amount of juice) and sugar.
Heat to boiling. Combine reserved juice and 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into cherry mixture.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add orange and almonds. Place chicken pieces in sauce, spoon sauce over, and simmer a few minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Add garlic and mushrooms. Sprinkle mushrooms with onion salt and add sherry and brown sugar. Saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve in broth with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: jo ella's cracker cookies
directions: Spread crackers on cookie sheet (leave crackers whole; don't break apart yet).
Melt butter and oleo and sugar; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour this mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(You might want to kind of lift off the cookie sheet so they don't stick.)
Break apart and serve!

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop fruits, nuts and candy fine and roll in a portion of flour.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk, then add rest of flour and soda.
Mix well.
Fold in candy, nuts, coconut and dates.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 275°.
Leave cake in tube pan and glaze while still hot.

title: sausage and pepper
directions: Slice onion, sausage and peppers.
Add all ingredients.
Place in oblong pan.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: crumb cake(frances zweighaft)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; set aside 1 cup of these crumbs and mix with cinnamon.
Add to remaining mix alternately 1 cup of milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in; do not beat.
Spread in shallow, greased pan.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 1/2 x 11-inch glass pan.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl beat eggs and 2 cups sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice; add alternately with dry ingredients, to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour half the batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Arrange half the apples over the batter.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar mixture over top.
Add remaining batter; top with apples and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cake cool 1 hour in pan; remove from pan, apple side up.
Cool to cut.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well in heavy cooker, stirring constantly over medium heat until thick; remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie shells (2 large ones or 3 smaller pie shells).
Beat egg whites, 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 7 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Bake 350° oven until brown.
Milk may be substituted with 1 large can evaporated milk and 3 cups water.

title: fudge
directions: Put marshmallow cream and vanilla in large bowl.
Put chocolate bits, sugar, butter and milk in large saucepan and heat on low. Start stirring at once and continue stirring for 10 minutes after mixture starts boiling.
Remove from heat; pour into container of marshmallow cream and stir vigorously.
When cool, stir in nuts and pour into pans or platters that have been buttered.
When cold, cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: lumpia
directions: Put all ingredients except pork in blender.
Chop ingredients very fine.
Mix in large bowl with pork.
Place mixture in small portions in lumpia shells.
Wrap.
Fry in half their depth of very hot oil.
Cook over low heat until shells are brown and crispy. Makes about 50.

title: meatballs(with blue cheese sauce)
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, egg, garlic and breadcrumbs; mix the ingredients evenly.
Form about 40 walnut size meatballs.
Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat; add meatballs.

title: coca-cola fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and place in skillet.
Mix Coke and ketchup; pour over chicken.
Bring to boil, then lower heat to simmer.
Let simmer until chicken is tender.
Makes the best barbecue chicken in town.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fry breakfast strips until crisp according to package directions.
Drain and crumble.
Line 10-inch quiche pan or pie pan with pastry.
Arrange crumbled strips and cheese on bottom of pan.
Combine Scramblers, milk and pepper. Pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted 2 inches from the edge comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, soup and lemon juice.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers and poppy seed.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve chilled.
Great over all meats, with eggs or as a dip.
Improves with age.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together thoroughly.
Stir in sugars.
Add and mix egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Roll dough in balls the size of walnuts and dip in water (one edge) and then in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put a chocolate kiss or egg left over from Easter, and press down.
Return to oven and bake 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: strawberry and cream cheese salad
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in bowl; mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in bowl; beat well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring until thawed. Chill until partially congealed.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill until firm.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: crawfish bateaux a la belle rose
directions: Mince the Cajun Trinity and saute in butter. When they turn clear, add 1 tablespoon flour and stir.
Add the Velveeta cheese and melt. Add the picante sauce and blend.
Before serving, blend in the parsley and green onions.

title: rich whipped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in eights. Place potatoes in large pot with enough salted cold water to cover potatoes. Bring to boil over high heat; reduce heat to medium. Cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until fork tender; drain potatoes. Return potatoes to pot; cook over low heat for 1 minute to dry out. Remove from heat. Heat cream and butter in small saucepan until butter melts; add salt and pepper. Add cream mixture to potatoes. Beat with mixture until fluffy, about 2 minutes; stir in parsley.

title: caramel rolls
directions: The night before thaw frozen bread dough (do not let rise). Flatten them out, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up jelly roll style and cut into 12 rolls, put in 9 x 12-inch pan that has nuts in bottom.
Melt together oleo, ice cream and brown sugar. Pour mixture over rolls and put in refrigerator until morning. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "new year's day" black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute meat and pour off grease.
Chop and saute celery, onion and bell pepper.
Add 2 cups cooked rice.
Add 2 cans jalapeno black-eyed peas.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cover with bread crumbs and butter in a casserole dish.
Bake until hot (approximately 350° for 20 to 30 minutes).

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Place cubed chicken in pan (8 x 8-inch).
Follow chicken with dressing made of croutons, butter, cream, onion, sage, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Top with gravy made of the broth, butter (2 tablespoons) and flour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: custard rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Top with crust and bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 375° until done.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Salt and pepper the roast very good.
Put in roast pan; fill with water, cover and cook at 300° for around 3 to 4 hours.
Add water if needed.
Take out for 30 minutes.
Put in refrigerator so grease will settle to top of pan.
Remove grease from top.
Bring to a boil in a pot, your broth, then add all your vegetables.
(Be sure to cook all your vegetables first.)
Add potatoes, carrots, cauliflower, corn, peas, green beans, onions, cabbage and celery. Then add the V-8 juice, stewed tomatoes and fines herbes.
Boil macaroni and barley; strain, then add to soup.
Let simmer for about 2 hours.

title: brunch quiche
directions: Beat eggs until frothy, then add cornstarch, cream, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Beat briskly.
Fold in cheese, bacon, onions and mushrooms.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Dribble the melted butter over the top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lazy man's mexican corn bread
directions: Beat egg (optional); add corn meal, picante sauce and enough milk to make it mix smoothly.
Spray an iron skillet or muffin pan with a nonstick cooking spray.
Pour in the corn bread mix and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.
For extra flavor, fry a few strips of bacon until very crisp and crumble these into the batter before cooking.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pour batter over butter, then add peaches.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and then add the remaining ingredients.
Put in mold and chill until firm.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam (13 x 9-inch size).
Cut steak in small pieces.
Cut potatoes in round slices.
Brown steak in frying pan and then place in baking dish.
Layer potatoes, green beans and then mix together the 2 soups and pour over meat and veggies.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix the peanut butter and butter.
Melt over heat in double boiler or microwave.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until light brown.

title: corn relish(canned)
directions: Combine corn, cabbage, red pepper, celery, onion, garlic, celery seed and spices in large kettle.
Stir in vinegar.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
If the relish is too thin mix 2 to 3 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup cold water and blend into relish, bring to a boil and continue cooking until liquid is thickened and smooth.
Stir constantly.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides from pan.
Remove and cool completely before slicing.

title: cinnamon crescents
directions: For filling, beat 3 egg whites until stiff peaks form; gradually beat in 2/3 cup of sugar.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fry bacon and cut into pieces. Start with lettuce and put layer after layer into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Let set 12 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl.
Combine whites, yogurt, applesauce, oil and zest.
Stir into dry mixture just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.

title: red cabbage and chestnuts
directions: Simmer these ingredients.
Cover until the chestnuts are tender.
Add to the cabbage mixture.
Cook these ingredients until well blended.
Serve hot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken livers
directions: Coat chicken livers with flour mixed with salt and pepper. Melt butter; saute chicken livers until golden brown.
Add scallions and mushrooms; cook until tender.
Add desired amount of sherry; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve livers on toast or rice. Makes four servings.

title: herbed linguine
directions: Bring 8-quarts water to boil; add 2 tablespoons salt and linguine.
Cook until pasta is al dente, tender but still firm to the bite.
(Fresh pasta will cook quickly in 2 to 3 minutes, dried pasta will take about 10 minutes.)
Drain and transfer to large bowl.
Toss with 1/2 cup olive oil.

title: quick lime cream pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk and lime juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine 1 can corn, eggs, sugar, pepper, butter, milk, cornstarch and salt in blender until well mixed.
Add second can of corn; pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes, until brown and firm.
This is a big dish.

title: kitchenette cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease and flour one 9 inch cake pan.
Mix all ingredients on medium speed until well mixed. Bake until golden brown or you can stick toothpick in center and it comes out clean.

title: french spring soup
directions: Melt butter in kettle.
Slowly saute scallion and onion until tender.
Add potatoes, carrot, 1 1/2 teaspoon salt and water. Cover and bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in rice and asparagus. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add spinach; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 4 teaspoons salt, pepper and cream.

title: chocolate chip cheese bars
directions: Cut cookie dough in half and press half of the dough onto the bottom of a greased 8-inch square pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg together and beat until smooth. Spread over crust. Crumble remaining dough over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the middle comes out clean. Cool before cutting. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Chill until it begins to set.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients. Turn into mold; chill to firm.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with tomatoes.
Serves 10.

title: buttermilk peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter a large plate, and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, bring the sugar, buttermilk, and salt to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cook to the soft ball stage, removing from the heat immediately when the candy thermometer reaches 234 degrees.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and stir with a wooden spoon to blend. Then beat energetically with the spoon until the fudge begins to lose its gloss and starts to thicken.
Pour quickly onto the plate.
Allow to cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: apple lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Combine sugar mixture, apple juice and lemon juice, stirring well.
Let lemonade mixture chill thoroughly.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
3 1/3 cups.

title: cincinnati five-way chili
directions: Salt a large cast iron skillet. Turn heat to medium and add meat, onions, and garlic.
Cook until all meat is browned.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, water and vinegar.
As mixture begins to boil, add everything else.

Adjust spices to taste, adding more salt if it needs perking up, turmeric and cumin for a sweatier chili flavor, cinnamon, cloves, and mace if you want it sweeter, cardamon for more bang, unsweetened chocolate for body.

title: pasta with shrimp and feta
directions: Cook pasta, drain and set aside; keep warm.
Saute shrimp and red pepper flakes in 2 tablespoons oil for 1 to 2 minutes, until shrimp are slightly pink.
Arrange shrimp in a baking dish; sprinkle with Feta cheese and set aside.
Add remaining oil in skillet; saute garlic over low heat.
Add tomatoes and juice. Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in wine,
basil, oregano, salt and pepper; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Spoon tomato mixture over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Garnish with fresh basil.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Combine flour, paprika and salt in a plastic bag. Add chicken and shake until well coated. Brown chicken on both sides in butter and oil. Add Sherry; cover and simmer about 25 minutes; or until tender. Combine cornstarch and cream, stir into pan. Cook, stirring until sauce thickens. Add lemon juice and wine. Sprinkle cheese over top of breasts, cover and let stand for 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: nellie's frozen corn
directions: Bring to boil 5 minutes.
Cool; package in containers with liquid.
Freeze.
Cook with margarine.
Season with pepper, if desired.

title: egg rolls
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Season with salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Blend in egg and soy sauce.
Beat mixture thoroughly.
At one end of the wrapper, spoon about 2 tablespoons of the mixture and roll tightly.
Brush end of wrapper with water to seal.
Deep fry.
Serve hot with sweet and sour sauce.

title: taco stuff
directions: Brown hamburger and chop into very small pieces.
Drain and put back in pan.
Drain and chop the tomatoes and put in pan.
Add all ingredients and heat over low fire.
Feeds approximately 8.

title: moravian christmas cookies
directions: Melt lard and add to molasses.
Add vinegar-soda mix.
Cut up butter and work with sugar and a little flour until there are no lumps.
Add to other mixture.
Add enough flour so you can stick finger in dough and it will not stick.
Roll paper thin on well-floured cloth.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake in 300° oven for 5 to 10 minutes, just until done.
Cool on pan a few minutes. Store in tightly covered box.
Makes about 200 cookies.

title: mushroom and cheese casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine for 5 minutes or until onion is clear.
Stir in bread cubes and Cheddar cheese. Pour into greased glass casserole dish.
Microwave on Medium-high for 10 minutes or bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and sugar together until creamy. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add the oatmeal and flour.
Then add chocolate chips.
Bake on
lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: my chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, celery, onion and bouillon until chicken is done.
Pull chicken out and cool.
Bring broth to boil and add vegetables and rice.
Cook vegetables until done.
Add cream of chicken soup. Stir in well.
Add chunks of chicken and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line dish with vanilla wafers, then row of sliced bananas, then filling.
Make another row of vanilla wafers, another row of bananas, then icing.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli separately according to their package directions.
Drain well.
Set aside.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine in order given.
Bake in 10 x 15-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pack mixture lightly into a 2-quart glass loaf dish.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread soup, mixed with milk, over alternated layers of potatoes, onions and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar in a medium bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture after each.
Add sour cream to mixture.
In another bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture, small portions at a time, alternately with milk.
Mix completely and well.
Add lemon and vanilla extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick after cake has baked 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool, then glaze cake.
Use Baker's Joy for tube pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: Crust:
Combine margarine, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar. Blend.
Pat dough in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend very well.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients (except eggs) in a heavy saucepan. Cook on the stove until the mixture thickens.
Remove from the stove and add beaten eggs (use a mixer).
Place the mixture back on the stove and cook until it has a pudding consistency.
Cool and skim the top.
Spoon pudding into dessert dishes.
(May be used as filling for chocolate pie.)

title: mom's marble cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in large bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each addition.
Remove 1 cup of batter.
Blend chocolate into 1 cup batter; set aside.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package; add 1 1/3 cups of coconut after beating.
Bake in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan at 350° about 20 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Place on serving tray.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Blend the softened cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Chop dried beef and onion and add to mixture.
Stir in horseradish. Chill and serve with raw vegetables.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss stuffing mix with melted butter; set aside.
Cook broccoli until almost tender; drain and set aside.
Combine cheese and soup; cook over medium heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.

title: watermelon slice cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and extract.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Set aside 1 cup of dough.
Tint remaining dough with red dye, wrap with plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours.
Tint 1/3 c. reserved dough with green dye, wrap and chill.
Wrap remaining dough and chill.

title: eclair cake
directions: Stir instant pudding with milk until thickened.
Add the Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the graham crackers.
Pour half of the filling over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers; pour rest of filling over them.

title: layered ice cream cake
directions: In bottom of a 13 x 9 cake pan put 4 ice cream sandwiches. Top with chocolate cool whip and crushed whopper candy. Repeat layering three times. Last layer put broken whopper candy on top of cool whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: In skillet, place onions, ground meat and sausage crumbled up. Cook until done, drain and set aside.
In same skillet, place sliced squash and cook it down until tender; drain squash and mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in casserole dish or large Dutch oven.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle crumbs.
Let set for cooling.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Smash the bananas, chop nuts, drain pineapple and mix with strawberries.
Add to jello.

title: mom's green tomato relish
directions: Chop or grind the tomatoes, onions and
sweet peppers medium. Add salt to taste.
Cook the remaining ingredients about 10 minutes. Add chopped ingredients and cook all for 10 minutes. Can and seal.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender; drain well.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender. Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted. Remove from heat; stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix sugar and melted butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in airtight bowl in refrigerator.
Dough is better when thoroughly cold or made the night before.
Grease muffin tins.
Spoon in dough.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for one week.

title: christmas custard(eggnog)
directions: Use part of milk to fix pudding according to directions.
Add whipping cream and sugar; mix.
Add rest of milk; beat 5 minutes. Delicious!

title: spice tea
directions: Mix thoroughly in mixing bowl and pour into airtight containers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together.
Press into a 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking pan.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: beef and mushroom quiche
directions: Partially bake pie shell on preheated cookie sheet at 450° for about 6 minutes.
Cook ground chuck and mushrooms until red color has disappeared.
Drain off fat.
Mix cheese, flour, salt, onion flakes and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix eggs and Pet milk.
Spoon meat mixture into pie shell.
Pour egg-milk mixture over the meat. Bake at 375° on cookie sheet until knife inserted comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tasty 'n tender round steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Combine flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Use to coat meat.
Save remaining flour mixture. Melt shortening in skillet and brown meat on both sides.
Push meat to one side. Stir in remaining flour mixture.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Keep in dry container.
To make tea, use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour in one cup of boiling water and cook mixture until clear.
Cool slightly and pour over fresh, hulled strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until chilled and serve with Cool Whip.
Just like Frisch's.

title: melt in your mouth pecan rolls
directions: In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and syrup. Spread in 2 greased 8 inch pans; set aside. Unroll each tube of dough into a rectangle. Seal seams. Combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over dough. Roll up jelly-roll style on long side. Seal edge. Cut each roll into 16 slices. Place cut slices down on prepared pans. Bake 375° for 13-17 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pans for 1 minute before inverting onto serving plates.

title: eggless banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo with graham crackers.
Press into baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Beat the rest of oleo with sugar and cream until smooth.
Spread evenly over crumbs.
Cover this with sliced bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over this.
Next cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries over Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
When first two mixtures are cool, add yeast mixture to beaten eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well. Mix remaining flour and mix well.
Mix, but do not knead.
Cover and let set in refrigerator at least two hours. Shape into rolls and put in greased pan.
Let rise in warm room until double in size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: hot cocktail canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Mound onto cocktail bread. Broil until puffed and browned (about 2 minutes).

title: white coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Add milk and flour alternately, stirring thoroughly.
Lastly, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake in 3 layers in moderately hot oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and egg strata
directions: Trim and butter bread.
Lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Spread ham over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Mix eggs, dry mustard, milk and a dash of salt and pepper. Pour over all.
Cover with foil. Let stand in fridge overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes. Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cashew meat loaf
directions: *Omit oil, if desired.

title: cheddar waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the apples and pecans.
Combine mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons sugar; add to apple mixture and mix well.
Combine raisins, cranberries and remaining sugar; sprinkle over apple mixture.
Top with cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking. Sift sugar and cocoa.
Pour melted mixture over sugar and cocoa. Stir well and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a large pan and spread.
This makes 6 pounds, but can be divided.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs and oil and stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, beat eggs; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir with whip.
Add cheese and spinach, mixing well.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° until firm when pan is shaken.
Cool 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into 40 squares.
Can be frozen for future use!

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given in large dishpan or bowl. Drop by ice cream scoop on lightly greased cookie sheet and flatten (6 per sheet).
Bake 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: taco bean salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet; drain.
Stir in beans, seasoning mix and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover. Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Best if prepared ahead and allowed to set overnight in refrigerator.
Good served with assorted vegetables.

title: old southern cornbread
directions: Pour mixture in pan.
Cook in oven until golden brown.
Can be served covered in brown bean broth.

title: garlic prawns
directions: Heat wok; add oil.
Add garlic and stir-fry briefly; do not brown.
Add prawns.
Stir-fry just until prawns turn pink.
Add green onions.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and sake; add to wok. Toss and cook until thickened.
Serve at once.

title: fudge scotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Press mixture into a very well greased 9 X 9 pan.
Bake for 30-35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes and cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: Place butter, garlic, lemon juice, parsley and salt in a shallow baking dish.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 2 minutes or until the butter has melted.
Add shrimp and cook, uncovered, 4 to 6 minutes on High (100%) until shrimp turn pink and are opaque.
Stir twice while cooking.
Serve over rice, garnished with peas and chopped red peppers.

title: seafood salad
directions: Check
crab meat for shells.
Drain canned shrimp.
Add to bowl,
crab meat, shrimp, sea legs, celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix
lightly.
Add
mayonnaise
and hard-cooked eggs. Salt to taste.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish; add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook meat with onions, bay leaves, salt and pepper until meat is done.
Shred meat and leave in broth, keeping enough broth to simmer barbecue.
Add rest of ingredients and heat until flavor is reached.
Serve on buns.

title: citrus punch
directions: In a punch bowl, stir together juices and ginger ale.
Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: cathy's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients before adding meat.
Brown meatballs in electric skillet.
Remove meatballs from skillet to make gravy.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken, set aside to cool and save broth.
Add more water, enough to cover egg noodles, and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil.
Add egg noodles.
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile saute mushrooms, celery, & carrots in butter.
When noodles are tender add mushrooms, celery, carrots and butter that you sauteed them in, add chicken, salt & pepper, and garlic.
Bring to a rolling boil. Add fresh parsley.
Serve hot.

title: orange creamsicle fluff
directions: Mix orange gelatin and 1 cup boiling water.
Drain oranges (put juice with cold water to make 1 cup) and add to gelatin.
Cool in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Whisk powdered pudding into gelatin. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add oranges.
Chill for at least 1 hour or long until set.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Shape into crescents and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.

title: homemade tandy kakes
directions: Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread 1 jar peanut butter right out of oven.
Let cool.

title: smothered liver
directions: Slice liver
thin; dip in boiling water for an instant, then drain.
Sprinkle
with seasoning;
roll in flour.
Fry in drippings; turn once.
Add hot water and green onions.
Reduce heat;
cover and cook 15 minutes.
Serve with grits.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil whole chicken; save broth.
Take chicken out of broth and debone.
Keep until after making noodles.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar
and
eggs well; in separate bowl mix flour, cream of
tartar,
baking soda and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to
shortening mixture and combine thoroughly. Shape into 1 inch
balls;
roll
into 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon
that	have
been
mixed
together. Place 2 inches apart on
greased
cookie
sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Rinse grapes.
Cut in half.
Remove seeds.
Put in bottom of large glass bowl.
Peel and slice bananas.
Spread over grapes. Drain peaches well.
Cut into small pieces.
Spread bananas. Rinse raspberries.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Peel oranges.
Remove white skin.
Slice into small pieces.
Spread over raspberries. Peel and slice kiwis.
Spread over oranges.
Pour orange juice over all.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: white mountain cream
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.

Place over low flame and stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils. Continue cooking until a small amount of syrup forms a soft ball in cold water or spins a thread when dropped from tip of spoon. Pour syrup in fine stream over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla; continue beating until mixture loses its gloss.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients
in a saucepan; simmer. Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour sauce over. Bake
for
hour	and 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken over halfway through.
Leave uncovered.	Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken mess
directions: Cut up and brown chicken in butter. Add 4 cups hot water. Bring to a boil. Add stuffing seasoning. Stir. Add stuffing crumbs. Mix well. Turn off heat. Let stand until water is absorbed. Fluff with fork. Top with turkey or chicken gravy.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add honey and beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining dry ingredients mixed together alternately with milk. Stir in fruit and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 325° for about 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: cheese ball el quicko
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple; roll in pecans and chill for an hour.
Serve on wheat crackers.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, then the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Spread half the mixture in a greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Cover with apples and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm and top with pudding sauce.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Add chocolate chips to prepared pancake mix.
Fry in hot, greased pan until bubbles form on surface, then turn and brown on other side.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and stir in dry ingredients, then pecans.
Dough should be thick.
Make rolls with dough and wrap in wax paper.
Keep refrigerated overnight and bake the next day, or whenever you wish to.

title: dump cake(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Mix and pour pineapple and pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Spread cake mix over mixture in dish.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together first 8 ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Toss to coat.
Cover.
Chill for 1 hour to blend flavors before serving.

title: ruby's punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well. Pour into punch bowl. Just before serving add Ginger Ale and sherbet.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute ground chuck; drain out excess grease in colander. Return to frypan and on low to medium heat, add onion, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Turn down to low heat and blend in soup. After blended, add sour cream; blend slowly and set on simmer.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles or any type of pasta you desire.

title: pasta bolognese
directions: In skillet, saute ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil until meat loses its pinkness.
Transfer to pan.
Peel and chop onion; dice celery and carrot.
Chop ham into small pieces.
Saute in remaining oil with onion, celery and carrot.
Transfer to pan with ground meat.
Combine.
Add water, tomato puree, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes.
Add chicken broth. Cook for a few more minutes.
Cook pasta according to directions. Drain well.
Serve immediately with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine red pepper, soup and sour cream; stir in chicken. Spoon into casserole dish and top with mixture of butter, cracker crumbs and poppy seeds.
Bake at 350 degrees about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese, Bisquick and hot sauce until well mixed. Form into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on ungreased cookie or baking sheet.
Serve hot.
May be frozen; these freeze well.
Just put in oven frozen and bake 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: Place berries in bowl.
Add lime juice and sugar.
Crush berries slightly.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Add pineapple juice. Put 1 quart of this mixture into punch bowl over block of ice. Add 3 bottles of ginger ale.
Serve.
As supply is depleted, add 1 quart of the fruit juice mixture and another 3 bottles of ginger ale.
Makes 200 (1/2-cup) servings.
Can make smaller amounts.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt chips on low heat.
Remove from heat and add noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken divan
directions: Poach 5 chicken breasts (boned, skinned and cut into bite size pieces).
(Poaching Method:
Put in saucepan and barely cover with water.
Add celery stalk and 1/2 medium onion; boil for 20 minutes.)
Place thawed broccoli on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken over broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs (dried), mixed with 2 tablespoons butter, melted.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Make a day ahead; refrigerate.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Cook meat together; drain off fat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Spread on open biscuits or rolls.

title: frankfurter-lima casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add eggs and mix lightly.
Put in shallow baking dish and top with crumbs.
Dot with margarine. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: sweet tooth bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Quarter biscuits.
Roll in cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg (mix ingredients before rolling biscuits).
Place biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and water; boil 2 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: firehouse chili
directions: In large pot brown ground beef.
In small frying pan, cook onions and bacon until onions are transparent.
Combine with ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients, being sure to add tomato juice last.
Cover and simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Serve topped with grated Cheddar and chopped onion. Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg together.
Mix milk and lemon extract, then mix remaining ingredients together, except raisins. Add the raisins, if desired.
Roll in balls (1 teaspoon).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
With a fork (dipped in flour), crisscross the ball, pressing it flat.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine and simmer all ingredients until cranberries pop (about 10 minutes).
Good with pork as well as turkey.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: roasted chicken legs with zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle the chicken parts with salt and pepper.
Brush them with melted butter and place them, uncut side down, on a rack in a large metal baking pan.
Roast for 30 minutes.
Turn over and roast for another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: the best dill pickles
directions: Wash and pack medium size cucumbers in clean quart jars.
Put fresh dill, garlic, etc. in jars to your own desired taste.

title: angel food cake
directions: Set out, but do not grease, a 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Measure and sift together the flour and confectioners sugar 3 times. Measure into a large mixing bowl the egg whites, cream of tartar and salt; beat until foamy.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons of sugar at a time, beating well.
Continue beating until meringue holds a stiff peak.
Fold in vanilla.
Fold in gradually the mixture of flour and sugar.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: souperior italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large baking pan, shape into loaf. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Use 4 cups of flour, adding one at a time.
Next add the jar of jelly, blending well. Use the 5th cup of flour to coat the fruit and then add to mixture, blending together well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
I use steeple pan and line it with wax paper.
Cook at 200° until done.
Yields 2 cakes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Stir in rice, mushrooms, carrots, almonds and salt. Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry.
Heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with minced parsley.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light.
Add flour and chopped walnuts.
Cream with spoon until mixture forms crumbs. Set aside 1 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Set pan on rack to cool.

title: slaw 2
directions: Chop up your cabbage.
(I do mine in a blender.)
Add enough mayonnaise to make it pretty juicy (about 7 or 8 tablespoons).
Add about 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Mix together well.
It is better after it gets cold.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple. Fold in bread cubes. Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon color, add sugar and milk. Sprinkle pudding mix over this and mix well.
Cook according to directions for the pudding.
Let set for 5 minutes then pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Add meringue and bake in 400° oven until meringue is browned.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles. Drain and cool. Add bell peppers, onion and olives. Stir. Pour Catalina dressing over top and mix well. Refrigerate until flavors blend.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend together flour, salt and shortening or butter.
Then add cold water.
Stir.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Roll out dough.

title: journey cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: valdosta muffins
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Put in ungreased muffin tins.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.

title: broccoli or cauliflower bake
directions: You can substitute cauliflower for broccoli.

title: jack-pot casserole
directions: Brown meat and cook noodles.
Drain noodles and then mix with corn and tomato soup.
Add all other ingredients together with the noodles.
Stir everything together and then place in oven at 350°; bake for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with more shredded cheese on top, if desired.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Quick and easy.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in sugar, a little at a time.
When creamy, add eggs (one at a time) beating well after each addition. Add almond and vanilla extract to milk.
Alternate milk and flour mixture (which has been sifted several times with baking powder), beating lightly until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in ungreased tube pan.

title: corn flake pudding
directions: Soak corn flakes and milk for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: coconut ambrosia salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients EXCEPT CHERRIES. Mix well and chill at least 1 hour before serving. Garnish with the cherries.

title: carrot cake and icing
directions: For cake:
mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in three greased
9-inch pans at 350 degrees until done.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Cast off ends.
Slice 1-inch thick.
Layer pickles, then sugar.
Add some garlic, cloves and allspice.
Add more sugar.
Continue until pickles are used.
Be sure to use all 5 pounds of sugar.
Refrigerate 7 days.
Stir and shake each day.

title: banana squares
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg yolks; mix well.
Add bananas.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Fold in nuts if desired.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream or banana slices.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients together with a little milk.
Add remaining milk; bring to a boil.
Thicken.
Add the vanilla.
Top with meringue.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar and mashed strawberries.
Beat at high for 15 minutes.
Add whipped cream. Put in graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: smoked pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; place in casserole.
Place onion slices on chops; sprinkle with salt and rice.
Combine soups; pour over pork chop mixture.
Add water.
Cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yield:
6 servings.

title: crisscross patch potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Cut potatoes in half longways.
Score approximately 1/4-inch deep crisscrosses along cut sides of each potato half.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place oleo and oil.
Heat until melted.
Place potatoes in pan with cut and scored side down.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine eggs and milk; add flour, baking powder and salt. Beat until smooth.
Pour through a funnel into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown (3 minutes).
Turn and fry one more minute. Go-o-o-d!!
Serves 8.

title: tail-gate blond brownies
directions: Sift together baking powder, soda and salt.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar; pour into large bowl and cool.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts and half of the chocolate pieces.
Spread into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with remaining chocolate, pressing slightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until mixture starts to pull away from edges.
Cool in pan and cut.

title: wild rice with shrimp and cilantro
directions: Rinse frozen shrimp in a colander with cold water; set aside to drain.
In a 12-inch skillet or large flameproof casserole, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and red and green peppers and cook, stirring occasionally, until limp, about 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic, hot water and rice; mix well.
Heat to boiling; stir. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in lime juice, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Serve, mounding slightly, on lettuce-lined plates with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cilantro.

title: pumpkin muffins with cream cheese
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat eggs; add sugar, pumpkin, oil and water.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Let stand one hour.
Put small amount of batter in muffin tins.
Put piece of cream cheese on top.
Top with batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 30 muffins.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Flatten slightly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese ramen salad
directions: In large bowl place chopped cabbage, sliced onions with tops, broken noodles (crush in pkg.), almonds, and sesame seeds. Mix remaining ingredients well. Pour over salad and toss. Serves 4-6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup and milk in pan.
Bring to boil slowly. Cook until small amount forms soft ball when dropped in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix, do not beat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat just until creamy and loses gloss.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: warmer kartoffel salat(hot potato salad)
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes. Saut onion in butter. Add water, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, potatoes and flour. Pour into covered casserole and bake in 275° oven for about 1 1/2 hours. Serves about 12. Real good reheated.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and garlic in butter.
Add meat (which you have had the butcher slice as thin as possible, about 1/8-inch thick and which you have cut into 1/2-inch squares, removing all fat) and brown.
Cover with wine, water and spices.
Simmer until tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add tomato sauce, soy sauce and mushrooms; simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Just before serving, carefully stir in sour cream and garnish with parsley.
This dish is best cooked in a Dutch oven and served over rice.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind and mix all ingredients, except mustard.
Cook 50 minutes.
Add mustard.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion together.
Put all ingredients together in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 can Chinese noodles and bake 10 more minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bananas and layer on top of crust.
Mix 1 stick of margarine, powdered sugar and eggs.
Spread over bananas.
Mix together Cool Whip, nuts and pineapple.
Spread over fluffy mixture.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat eggs, Crisco and sugar. Add baking powder, flour and anise.
Mold any shape.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to margarine; mix well.
Blend eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually to eggs and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: salsa #1
directions: Place chopped tomatoes, peppers, onions, garlic and salt in crock.
Let stand for 10 to 12 hours, preferably overnight.
Boil vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil only 5 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 pints.

title: white frosting(must use an electric mixer)
directions: Combine (whisk) milk and flour in a sauce pan or microwavable bowl.
Cook on low to medium heat until thick.
Do Not Allow to Brown or Scorch.
Mixture will be very thick.
Cool completely.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Take cubed steak, 2 x 2-inch piece.
Roll 1/4 piece of onion and 1/2 slice bacon inside of cube steak.
Brown in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Then simmer with 1 quart of V-8 juice and seasonings, sliced thin celery, onion, carrots, garlic salt and powder, salt and pepper.
Then thicken with 2 tablespoons of cornstarch when cooked until done.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Add shortening, salt, sugar and yeast to lukewarm water.
Add flour and baking powder.
Make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth on well floured board.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with a 2-inch cutter.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Let rise in a warm place until ready to bake.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Makes 24.
Brush with melted butter.

title: devonshire cream
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in sour cream and powdered sugar until well mixed. Refrigerate until serving time. Serve on scone with strawberry preserves. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lamb breast, barbecued
directions: Cut lamb into five pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Place in a hot skillet and let fatty sides get brown.
Mix chili sauce, red pepper, vinegar and water and pour over lamb.
Slice onion and add to mixture.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, then remove lid and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes or until barbecue sauce is almost absorbed.
Serves 4.

title: stove top pot roast
directions: Melt shortening in heavy pot large enough to hold roast (with cover).
When shortening is hot, place roast (which is rubbed with all the seasoning) into pot.
Brown roast on all sides.
Turn to low heat.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours.
Add onions (sliced or chopped) to roast one hour before it is done.

title: "company is coming"(coconut cake)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Add the cream of tartar and beat until stiff. Add sugar and beat. Add crackers, nuts and vanilla. Bake in buttered oblong 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes. (Allow cake to cool well.)
Whip the preserves into the Cool Whip and spread over cooled cake.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Chill several hours.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Keeps well in refrigerator several days.
Also may be frozen several weeks.

title: insanity plea nutty marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir chopped pecans, flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and egg in large bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Spoon Marshmallow Creme over hot layer.
Let stand 1 minute; spread evenly.
Drizzle topping over Creme; sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups peanuts.

title: tornado cake
directions: Mix and cream sugar, eggs, fruit cocktail, baking soda and flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost while still hot.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake 1 deep-dish pie shell for 10 minutes at 400°. Slice tomatoes on bottom of pie shell. Sprinkle basil and oregano to taste over tomatoes. Spread onion on top of tomatoes. Mix mayo and cheese and spread over pie. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Sift flour; mix all dry ingredients well.
Add oil and eggs. Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Cook in greased and floured 9 x 11-inch cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken a la cathy
directions: Make chicken broth by steaming chicken in 2 cups water. Debone chicken.
Heat cream of mushroom soup, chicken a la king, chicken broth and 1/2 pound American cheese.
Add mushrooms, then cook broccoli and spaghetti as directed on packages.

title: chicken and squash casserole
directions: Mix melted butter with stuffing.
Pat 1/2 into greased baking dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Put on top and then put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: betty's pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and eggs together.
Add crushed pineapple, coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Combine curry powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over chicken.
In 10-inch skillet, combine orange juice, rice, water, brown sugar, mustard and remaining salt; mix well.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mr. green's beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Break up bread and fry in the butter until browned.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over bread.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot as a vegetable.

title: old timey chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter slowly. Combine eggs and sugar. Add butter and chocolate to eggs and sugar. Add vanilla. Pour into an unbaked graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool. Top with whipped topping and serve.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Then add flavoring.
Pour batter into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sugarless brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in vanilla. Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, beating until smooth.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine and press crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice together.
Sift 1/4 cup flour and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Pour over warm baked crust and bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool, then cut.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&Ms reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop by teaspoonful or shape into 1 inch balls and place on ungreased baking dish.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&Ms as desired.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 min. Yield:
5-6 dozen.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake at 375°.

title: cheezy biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Microwave Cheez Whiz as directed on package; pour into a small bowl.
Dip each biscuit top in the Cheez Whiz.
Dip biscuits in Parmesan cheese, coating tops completely.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie tin.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Stir in seasoning mix according to directions on package. Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth with blender.
Pour on top of meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and tomatoes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.
After done, top with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce and shredded cheese.

title: hawaiian meat balls
